title: party dip
directions: Mix and serve.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 16 tablespoons. Per tablespoon:
18 calories, 0.5 mg cholesterol, 0.03 g fat, 247 mg Na.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Make a paste of cocoa and food coloring.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Combine sifted flour with salt.
Add with buttermilk and vanilla to mixture alternately.
Fold in vinegar and soda.
Pour into three 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: aunt pat's onion rings
directions: Slice onions and pull apart in rings.
Have 4 bowls, 1 with milk, 1 with flour, 1 with egg and milk and 1 with cracker meal. Dip onion rings in each bowl and lay out on cookie sheet.
Let set for a couple of hours before frying.
Deep fry.
Can be frozen after frying.

title: crunchy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, butter, molasses, egg yolk and vanilla.
Stir in flour and half of the chocolate chips.
Mix and press dough into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake until golden brown (about 20 to 25 minutes).

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in water to cover until tender, about 20 minutes.
Set potatoes aside until cool enough to handle, then peel and slice.
Put potatoes in a large bowl.
Saute bacon in a large skillet until browned and crisp.
Remove bacon from skillet and reserve.
Remove all but 8 tablespoons bacon grease from skillet.
Set skillet over medium-high heat; add onion and saute, stirring often, for about 3 minutes.
Stir in flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Slowly stir in vinegar and 1/2 cup water. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens, 1 to 2 minutes.

title: roast pork tenderloin
directions: Combine herbs and garlic; set aside.
Brush tenderloins with butter and roll in herb mixture, coating evenly.
Place tenderloins, fat side up, on a rack in a shallow roasting pan. Insert meat thermometer into thickest part of tenderloin, making sure thermometer does not touch fat.
Drizzle any remaining butter over meat.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: double crust chicken pot pie
directions: Fit 1 pie crust into 1 9-inch pie plate (according to package directions).
Do not bake.
Combine chicken and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into pie shell.
Moisten edges of pastry with water.
Place remaining crust on top.
Fold edges under and flute. Cut slits in top.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: yam delight
directions: Mix together the crushed pretzels and 2 sticks melted margarine.
Put in 2 pie pans or one oblong dish.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: fruit squares
directions: Melt butter in 15 1/2 X 10 1/2 X 1-inch jelly roll pan. Sprinkle on crumbs (tap sides of pan to distribute crumbs evenly). Sprinkle on coconut.
Distribute candied fruit as evenly as possible over the coconut.
Cut dates into a small amount of flour so they won't stick together.
Distribute dates over candied fruit. Sprinkle on nuts.
Press mixture lightly with hands to level pan. Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over the top.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.
Remove from pan.
Makes about 54 (1 1/2-inch) squares.

title: eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding mix and stir together with Cool Whip.
Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Put 1/2 of pudding mix over graham crackers.
Top with 2nd layer of graham crackers.
Cover with remaining pudding mix.
Top with 3rd layer of graham crackers.
Frost with Fudge Frosting.

title: everyday easy broccoli bake
directions: Combine soup, milk and soy sauce.
In 10 x 6-inch pan, layer 1/2 broccoli, 1/2 soup mixture and 1/2 onions.
Top with remaining broccoli and soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Blend Crisco and sugar.
Combine soup with water and baking soda.
Add this to Crisco/sugar mix alternately with dry ingredients. Stir in raisins.
Bake in a greased pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: reception punch
directions: Mix and add to syrup. Serves 20.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Start with all ingredients, except vegetables.
Cook on high heat until it boils; stir often.
Turn down heat to simmer.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes or longer.
Add frozen vegetables; simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chinese pork dumplings
directions: Soak mushrooms in warm water until soft, about 30 minutes; drain.
Rinse in warm water; drain.
Remove and discard stems; chop caps finely.
Mix mushrooms, pork, bamboo shoots, green onions, egg white, cornstarch, salt, 2 teaspoons soy sauce, 1/2 teaspoon sesame oil and the white pepper.

title: easy brownies
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
In a bowl, mix sugar, flour, cocoa, eggs and vanilla.
Pour in melted margarine and mix well.
Pour back into pan and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes. Real rich!
Also doubles well to go in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sweet chunk pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and place whole cucumbers in crock.
Cover with boiling water and let stand overnight.
Drain and repeat this procedure on the next 3 mornings.
On the fifth day, drain and slice into 1/2-inch chunks.

title: microwave 2 minute fudge
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla until partially blended.
Put butter over top in center of dish.
Microwave on High power 2 minutes.
Stir well until smooth.
Pour into greased 8-inch square dish.
Chill 1 hour.
Makes 36 squares.

title: grumpy's gazpacho(serves 4)
directions: Combine all ingredients except sour cream and chives. Chill thoroughly and serve in chilled cups or bowls.
Top with sour cream and sprinkle with chives.

title: creamy chicken vegetable chowder
directions: Combine milk, chicken broth and both the canned soups in a 4-quart saucepan.
Blend well.
Add chicken, onions, corn, chiles and mushrooms.
Mix well.
Cook over medium heat for 5 to 8 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
tags: whole kernel corn with sweet peppers

title: fruit diabetic cookies
directions: Boil dates, prunes and raisins (that have been cut up) in a saucepan until thick.
Add the oleo and leave until cool.
Beat in the eggs, then dry ingredients.
Then add vanilla, chopped nuts, cereal and coconut.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350°.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Blend items in blender.
Use as a dip for raw carrot sticks, celery, cauliflower, radishes, pepper strips, scallions, etc.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs and bananas together and beat 2 minutes.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Mix
all together and beat 2 or 3 minutes longer.
Bake in loaf pan
at
for 1 hour.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in water for 5 minutes or until tender; drain. Beat eggs in large bowl until foamy.
Add mayonnaise, onion and green pepper to eggs.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix cheese with zucchini.
Add to egg mixture; mix well.
Pour into 6 cup shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried cabbage and shells
directions: Fry bacon in frying pan.
Remove fried bacon, but not the grease.
Slice cabbage into 6 quarters, then separate cabbage leaves and put in frypan with bacon grease.
Cover frypan and cook over medium heat until tender (about 10 to 15 minutes).
Add cooked drained macaroni and fried bacon to cabbage.
Cook covered in frypan for 10 minutes over medium heat, stirring periodically to avoid mixture burning.
This can be used as a side dish or as a meal.

title: coffee cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Remove 1/2 cup of mixture to sprinkle on top of cake before baking.
Add the baking powder, soda, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and nutmeg to remaining mixture.
Add eggs and sour milk; beat until smooth.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) greased cake pans.

title: poppy seed dessert bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Add eggs, milk, oil and extracts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 60 minutes.
Cool on wire rack for 15 minutes before removing from pans.

title: doubly bubbly
directions: Combine all ingredients; add 1 tray of ice cubes.
Serves 20.

title: nicki's raisin bites
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Fold in raisins, drop by teaspoonful on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields approximately 5 dozen.

title: jim's minestrone soup
directions: You will need a water-filled cauldron.

title: avocados and shrimp
directions: Toss the
shrimp
with all ingredients, except the last three listed.
Chill
shrimp mixture for 24 hours.
Remove bay leaves and
strain
shrimp
mixture.
Sprinkle
diced avocados with lime juice.
Add avocados to the strained shrimp mixture. Serve on lettuce lined plates.
Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine bread cubes and 1 cup crumbs.
Stir in broth, eggs, salt, celery, onion, chicken and mushrooms.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Melt butter or margarine and combine with 1/2 cup crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 6 to 8.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time. Beat well after each.
Add whipping cream.
Beat just enough to mix.
Add flour.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: the veggie dish
directions: Line a glass dish with potatoes; place green beans on top. Then add corn and meat.
Mix soup and milk together; pour over vegetables.
Top with grated cheese.
Cook on High in microwave for 8 minutes; let stand 2 minutes and then cook on Medium-high for an additional 2 minutes.

title: chocolate chip chocolate drops
directions: Beat eggs; add soda and melted margarine.
Stir in cake mix until well moistened.
Stir in chocolate chips (and nuts if desired).
Pinch off dough to form balls a little smaller than a walnut.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 13 minutes.
Cool.
Sift powdered sugar over tops. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake in two layers at 325°.

title: aunt jenny's cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and chill before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes the night before.
Next day, grated potatoes and mix with onions.
Set aside.
Melt margarine and cheese in a pan. In a small bowl, mix sour cream and milk.
Add this to cheese mixture, then add to potatoes in a casserole.
Top with crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mommy's casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
In a frying pan, brown meat and onion.
Drain excess oil.
Combine meat, onion, macaroni, corn and tomato soup in a casserole dish. Top with cheese slices.
Bake, covered, in a 350°
oven for 1/2 hour.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: broccoli salad
directions: I chill my broccoli in ice water and drain well.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: lisa's buttermilk biscuits
directions: Stir dry ingredients into bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk; stir quickly.
Knead.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch.
Cut out 12 biscuits.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Pour boiling water over jello, stirring until jello is dissolved.
Add orange sherbet, stir until melted.
Stir in 1 can of mandarin orange segments (1 cup).
Pour into 6-cup ring mold, chill until firm.

title: basic surprise
directions: Combine oleo and sugar; beat in egg.
Add flour using mixer. Make small balls and flatten.
Put in cherries, nuts, dates or wafers.
Roll into balls.
Roll in coconut and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Check often.

title: buckeyes
directions: Cream butter, sugar and peanut butter together.
Add Rice Krispies.
Make into balls.
Dip into melted semi-sweet chocolate.

title: ham and cheese muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease and flour 12 medium muffin cups. Beat milk, oil and egg slightly in a large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients with fork until moistened.
Divide batter among cups. Bake until golden brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into 1-inch balls; flatten with fork.
Bake 350 degrees for 8-10 minutes.
Should be slightly brown on the edges.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen.

title: german bundt cake
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg yolks separately.
Mix in extracts.
Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
After greasing and flouring Bundt pan, embed almond in each crease. Pour in batter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: super-easy crab dip
directions: Put the cream cheese in a dish.
(You can even leave it as it is.)
Top with crab or shrimp, drained.
Pour cocktail sauce over it.
Stick a knife in it and serve with crackers.

title: oysters mosca
directions: Saute onion, celery and garlic in butter; add seasoning and oysters.
When edges curl, add liquid, then fold in bread crumbs. Put in casserole; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese or buttered bread crumbs or both.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese chile roll
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Roll Velveeta between 2 pieces wax paper until about 1/2-inch thick.
Spread cream cheese mixture on top of Velveeta.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Keep cold until about 20 minutes before serving.
Serve with crackers. Makes large roll.

title: sausage bread
directions: Combine browned sausage, eggs, pepperoni, cheeses and parsley. Roll pizza dough in rectangle shape.
Place mixture lengthwise down center of dough.
Fold back over, then tuck in ends.
Fold front over. Roll onto cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
Using reserved egg yolk, brush over crust. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Slice and serve warm or cold as appetizer.

title: hillbilly salad
directions: Sprinkle Jell-O straight from box on the cottage cheese and let stand for 1/2 hour.
Then add can of Mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Fold in 9 ounces of Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts or coconut.

title: lemon cheese bars(cheesecake cookies)
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly.
Reserve one cup of cake mixture and pat the rest into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and 1 egg and spread over crust.
Sprinkle top with reserved crumbs.
Bake 15 minutes more.
Cool completely and cut into bars.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients except candy Kisses.
In large bowl, mix on lowest speed with electric mixer or by spoon until dough forms.
Shape dough into balls, using a rounded teaspoonful for each.
Roll balls in granulated sugar, then place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes; don't overbake. Top each immediately with candy Kiss; press firmly so cookie cracks around edges.
Let cool.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine the brown sugar and flour, mixing well. In a large bowl, combine eggs, corn syrups, vanilla, and melted butter. Beat with a fork.
Add the sugar mixture and mix well.

Sprinkle the pecans over the bottom of the pie crust. Pour the filling on top of the pecans. As the pie bakes, the pecans will rise to the top. Bake for 55 to 60 minutes, until filling is set and pecans are golden brown.
Cool before slicing.

title: frozen pudding bars
directions: Prepare pudding mix with milk as directed on package.
Pour into paper or plastic cups to mold.
Insert wooden stick.
Freeze about 5 hours.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Dice celery, green pepper and onion.
Drain macaroni; add all ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Separate eggs and beat whites until stiff; set aside.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add alternately with flour.
Beat well.
Add coconut, nuts and extracts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: pumpkin swirl cheesecake(makes 10 to 12 servings)
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press onto bottom and sides of 9-inch pan.
Combine cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Reserve 1 cup of cheese mixture; add pumpkin, remaining sugar and spices to remaining cheese mixture.
Mix well.
Layer half of pumpkin mixture and half of cheese mixture over crust; repeat layers.
Cut through batter with knife several times for marble effect.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Loosen cake from rim of pan; cool before removing rim of pan.
Chill.

title: pineapple squash bake
directions: Thaw squash; combine with drained pineapple, 4 tablespoons brown sugar and salt.
Put in 1-quart casserole; dot top with butter.
Sprinkle with remaining brown sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: 2 egg custards
directions: Beat eggs slightly; mix flour and sugar together real good and add to eggs.
Then, add milk, vanilla and salt.
Add all these together.
Bake crusts until set, then pour in the egg mixture and bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Turn oven back to 350°.
Bake about 20 more minutes or until done, when knife is inserted in center and comes out clean.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs with buttermilk; mix well.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Debone chicken breasts and pound to flatten.

Mix the cream cheese, garlic, dill, parsley, salt, Tabasco sauce and lemon juice. Divide into 6 equal portions and place in center of chicken breasts. Roll breasts and place close together in baking dish. Combine wine and chicken broth.
Pour over breasts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: homemade lemon pie
directions: Mix egg yolks and milk in top of double broiler.
Mix sugar and flour, and add to eggs and milk.
Stir over boiling water until thickened.
Add grated lemons, and margarine.
Pour into pie shells.
Add vanilla flavoring.

title: heart healthy coffee cake(lo-fat)
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, soda, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and salt.
Set aside.
In a big bowl, toss together chopped apples and egg substitute. Stir in sugar, 1/4 cup nuts and applesauce. Add flour mixture and stir just enough to mix it.
Pour batter into a 9-inch round baking pan.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover casserole for the first 45 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail. Soften gelatin in lemon juice, then dissolve over hot water. Blend cream cheese with mayonnaise and salt. Stir in gelatin. Whip cream until stiff, adding sugar gradually during last stages of beating. Fold in cheese mixture, nuts and fruit cocktail. Place in mold of your choice and freeze until firm (overnight). Turn out onto platter and garnish with watercress.

title: peperonata
directions: Cook and stir onions in oil in 10-inch skillet until tender; add remaining ingredients except tomatoes.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes; cover and simmer until green pepper is tender, about 5 minutes.
Garnish with ripe olives.

title: james' mexican cornbread
directions: Beat eggs; add corn, cornmeal, oil, soda, salt and milk.
Fold in onion, pepper, celery, black pepper and chili powder.
Pour in a 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: punch for 35
directions: Tie spices in cloth bag and simmer in the water for 10 minutes.
Remove bag, add 1 lemon, sliced thin and the brown sugar; simmer about 15 minutes to make a syrup.
Add the rest of the ingredients to the syrup and bring to boiling.
Serve hot or cold.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add beaten eggs.
Blend rest of ingredients.
Take tablespoon of dough for each cookie.
Put flour on hands so dough won't stick.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Put on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 36 cookies.
A good cut-out cookie.

title: solo coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together well with mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and sour cream by hand.
Add baking powder, salt and flour.
Mix well.
This will make batter stiff.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: In skillet over medium heat, brown meat and onion until done. Pour off drippings; stir in corn, tomato sauce, rice, steak sauce and black pepper.
Set aside.
Cut tops off peppers.
Remove seeds.
Spoon in mixture; arrange in 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until peppers are done.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Bake chicken at 350° for 30 minutes.
Drain fat.
Mix remaining ingredients together; pour over chicken.
Bake an additional 45 minutes, basting several times.

title: cheese bells
directions: Gluh Wein is sold from stalls at the famous Nuremburg Christmas Market.
All the stalls are in the open air and it is cold!
The hot wine warms you to your toes and you are able to watch the animated clock and the pageant without freezing.
The stalls sell ornaments, crafts and most anything to do with Christmas for decorating, cooking or gifts.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine first 7 ingredients; simmer for 8 to 10 minutes.
Add beef, 3 ounces cheese and rice.
Stir until cheese melts.
Spray pan with Pam.
Pour into pan and sprinkle with rest of cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Let sit for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dressing for cabbage
directions: Boil all ingredients the let cool. Pour over shredded cabbage. Left over dressing may be stored in the refrigerator.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix sugar with juices.
Pour in water.
Place tea and spices in cloth bag.
Add to water.
Let steep 20 minutes.
Remove bag. Serve hot.
Makes 20 to 24 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Drain well.
In a casserole dish, add ground beef and soup.
Top with Tater Tots. Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven, or until Tater Tots are golden brown.
Add cheese and return to oven just long enough for cheese to melt.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Peel and pull onion rings apart.
Cook in butter in skillet until transparent.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, add layer of onions, Parmesan cheese, crushed Ritz crackers and pats of butter on crackers.
Continue another layer, ending with butter on crackers.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and line pan with 1/2 of crumb mixture.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Chill until set.
Put Carnation milk in freezer, in shallow pan, until it starts to freeze.
Then beat until stiff and add jello.
In another bowl, beat cream cheese with 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Fold cheese mixture into jello mixture and beat until smooth.
Add crushed pineapple.
Pour into lined pan.
Top with remaining half of crumb mixture.
Chill overnight.

title: blueberry trifle
directions: Crush vanilla wafers; set aside.
Mix condensed milk, softened cream cheese, Cool Whip and lemon juice until smooth.
In trifle bowl, put half of wafers; layer cream cheese mixture and layer of blueberry pie filling.
Repeat layers.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Extra Cool Whip can be put on top when ready to serve (optional).

title: chicken donatich
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces and bread.
Fry chicken in hot oil and drain.
Bake chicken pieces with a small amount of butter for 15 minutes on 350°.
Add chopped garlic, vinegar, tarragon, chicken broth, white wine, salt and pepper, and artichoke hearts (cut into smaller pieces) with the juice.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve on a bed of rice.

title: low-fat chocolate eclairs(only fat from frosting and graham crackers)
directions: Mix contents of both boxes pudding with skim milk until thick. Prepare Dream Whip according to directions (use skim milk).
Fold Dream Whip into pudding.
Layer bottom of baking dish (9 x 13 x 2-inch) with graham crackers.

title: fancy cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to
Oil a 10-inch round pie pan and place in oven to heat.

title: cherry dream salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in double boiler until smooth.
Let cool.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine butter and flour in a saucepan over low heat; gradually add chicken broth and cream of chicken soup.
Stir in chicken, salt, pepper and mixed vegetables.
Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with one of the pastries.
Add the chicken mixture and cover with second pastry.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until pastry is golden brown.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Shred all cheese together; add pimentos.
Mix well.
Add all other ingredients, mixing until smooth.
Chill 1/2 hour before serving.
Serve on toasted bread or crackers.

title: ooie gooie butter cake
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Blend next 3 ingredients and pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve when cooled.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients except nutmeg in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Place in greased casserole.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Set casserole in a pan of water.
Bake 90 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Mix flour, cocoa and cinnamon together.
Add eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla and soda. Then add flour 1 cup at a time with buttermilk and zucchini.
Bake in 10 x 15-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle on chocolate chips and nuts. Frost within 15 minutes after baking.

title: sausage patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape to form about 3 1/2-inch rounds and 3/8-inch thick.
Pan-fry over medium heat for about 5 minutes per side.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake sugar cookie mix in pizza pan.
While cookie is baking, mix glaze.

title: chicken enchilada soup
directions: Heat oil in a pot over medium heat and saute onion and garlic. Add relish and chicken broth and cook with pot covered for 15 minutes over low heat.
Add cream, salt and chicken.
Simmer another 8 to 10 minutes over low heat.
Stir in cheese and serve hot.

title: asparagus with mustard-dill sauce
directions: Combine all but asparagus.
Cook asparagus until barely tender; cool in ice water and place on oval platter.
Spoon some sauce over asparagus and serve balance in gravy boat.

title: grandma robbie's fried chicken nuggets
directions: Heat oil in frying pan.
Season pancake mix with salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in egg and the pancake flour and fry until golden brown.

title: date balls
directions: I mash the dates as I cook this mixture.
Cook the first 4 ingredients over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add Rice Krispies and chopped nuts.
When cool enough to handle, make into small balls and roll in Angel Flake coconut.

title: taos inn corn chowder
directions: Cut potatoes in 1/2-inch dice.
Cover them with water by about 1-inch in large saucepan.
Simmer until tender.

title: marbled cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch baking pan in oven.
After margarine is melted, remove from oven.
Press crushed Oreo cookies firmly and evenly.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Pour half of the batter evenly over prepared crust.
Stir melted chocolate into remaining batter; spoon over vanilla batter.
With table knife or spatula, gently swirl through batter to marble.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Chill.
Cut into bars.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and beaten egg yolks.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk; dredge berries and nuts in flour.
Add spices. Beat in egg whites and mix all together.
Makes 3 (9-inch) layers. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: velvety custard pie
directions: Thoroughly mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly stir in hot milk.
At once, pour into unbaked pie shell.
Dash top with nutmeg.
Bake in very hot oven (475°) for 5 minutes; reduce heat to 425 and bake for 10 minutes longer or until knife inserted halfway in center comes out clean.
Cool on rack.
Serve cool or at room temperature.
Yields 1 pie.

title: gooey butter cake(chocolate or vanilla)
directions: Melt butter (margarine) in a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Mix box of cake mix with 3 eggs.
The dough will be stiff but spread over melted butter to form crust.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 2 eggs. Mix well with low speed mixer.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 325° until done, about 30 minutes.
If using chocolate, bake 20 minutes, then spoon white mixture more evenly over chocolate.
Bake 10 more minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: corned beef ball
directions: Mix and roll in balls.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Saute onions in oil for 2 minutes.
Add soy sauce, sugar and 1 1/2 cups water; heat to boiling.
Simmer, uncovered 15 minutes or until onions are tender.
Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup water. Gradually stir into onion mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened.
Keep warm.
Mix ground beef and salt and pepper.
Shape into four 1-inch thick patties.
Place patties on rack in broiling pan; broil 4 minutes on each side or until done.
Place patties in casserole dish and spoon onion mixture on top and keep warm in oven until ready to serve.

title: vegetable bar
directions: Spread crescent rolls on pan.
Bake until done (about 10 minutes); cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing. Spread on rolls.
Top with all vegetables.
Cut into squares.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over butter, sugar and salt.
Stir to mix well.
Cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Beat in eggs and add to cooled mixture.
Add flour. Mix well.
Let rest in refrigerator over night.
Roll dough out to thickness of 1/4 inch. Cut rolls with biscuit cutter 2 hours before baking. Preheated oven at 450 degrees.
Bake rolls for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Rolls can be frozen before they are cooked.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and cream of potato soup.
Add shrimp, onion, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Blend until smooth.
Spread 1/2 of shrimp mixture into bottom of buttered deep dish pie pan. Sprinkle with almonds and half of grated cheese.
Add remaining shrimp mixture.
Sprinkle remaining Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Great with crackers or potato chips.
Best when served hot.

title: wendy's chili
directions: Brown beef; drain off fat.
Using a fork, crumble the cooked beef into pea-sized pieces.
In a large pot, combine beef and all the remaining ingredients and bring to a simmer over low heat. Cook 2 to 3 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: coffee cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together and set aside.
Cut oleo, sugar, salt and vanilla together and mix until crumbly.
Take 3/4 cup of this mixture for topping and set aside.
Bread eggs and add milk to flour mixture.
Beat until creamy.
Bake in a greased pan. Sprinkle crumbly mixture over top and add a sprinkle of cinnamon. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: gluhwein
directions: Mix juice from lemons and oranges with wine and sugar.
Simmer until nice and warm.

title: pretzel
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together; set aside.
In another bowl, mix the yeast, warm water, warm milk and egg yolks.
Mix everything together, except egg whites, raisins and brown sugar. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out thin, like pie crust.
Spread on stiffly beaten egg whites, brown sugar and raisins on half the dough.
Fold over; pinch dough together at edges.
Put small slits in top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Powdered sugar or glaze topping is optional.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Place egg whites in shallow bowl.
Place 1/2 cup of cornstarch in a shallow dish.
Dip chicken pieces in egg whites and coat with cornstarch.

title: dreamsicle cake ii
directions: Follow the recipe on the box, substituting milk instead of water. Also, use orange extract. Bake in 2 round cake pans. Cut layers in half after cooled.

title: zucchini chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream together sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add zucchini, chips and nuts.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Grease and flour pans.
I use 2 loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: pepper relish
directions: Wash and prepare peppers and onions. Grind in food mill. Combine with other ingredients. Boil 30 minutes. Pack in jars and seal.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes and mix with all ingredients, except the 1/4 cup butter and corn flakes. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan; top with butter and corn flakes mixed. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours. Will keep for several days.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Crumble angel food cake in bowl. Mix cream cheese and
Cool Whip together and add to cake.
Pat into 13 x 9 pan and add strawberries to glaze and then pour over cake mixture.
Chill.

title: roasted spiced turkey breast
directions: Combine all ingredients, except turkey, in large shallow pan or bowl.
Add turkey; marinate for 1 hour in refrigerator, turning once.
Discard unused marinade.
Cover the breasts with foil; roast for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Baste occasionally. Uncover; roast for an additional 30 to 40 minutes, until brown.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in large saucepan.
Drain.
Pour soups and sauce over meat.
Stir and heat thoroughly.
Empty chips into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour heated mixture over the chips.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 450° until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fried zucchini sticks
directions: Stir together bread crumbs, cheese, onion salt and garlic powder in medium bowl.
Stir together egg whites and water in small bowl.
Pour corn oil into heavy 3-quart saucepan or deep frying, filling no more than 1/3 full.
Heat over medium heat at 375°.
Dip zucchini sticks in egg mixture, then coat with crumbs.
Carefully add to oil in single layer.
Fry about 1 minute, turning once, or until crisp and lightly browned.
Drain on paper towel and serve.

title: dry spice tea mix
directions: Mix in	jar.
Can be used by teaspoon or made in larger quantity.
Orange
juice,
cranberry,
etc. can be added.
Can add peppermint or cinnamon stick, orange and lemon slices.

title: egg nog
directions: Place all ingredients, except ice cubes, into blender container.
Cover and process at liquefy.
With motor running, remove feeder cap and add ice cubes, one at a time.
Continue to process until smooth.

title: english trifle
directions: Thaw strawberries. Drain peaches. Cut pound cake in half lengthwise. Cut each half crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.

title: super quick "danish" pastries
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Make a well and add egg and milk.
Stir until smooth; it may be necessary to add more milk to get a batter that can hold its shape.

title: lite chocolate eclair cake
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch lasagna dish or pan.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Uncover and brown, about 15 minutes.

title: crunchy drop cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat together the brown sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Blend egg, milk and vanilla. Add combined flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in cereal.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire cooling rack.
Store in loosely covered container.

title: crumb cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° until done.

title: garlic croutons
directions: Spread butter or margarine over both sides of bread slices; sprinkle with garlic powder.
Cut into 3/4-inch cubes.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes or until croutons are crisp and dry.
Let croutons cool, then store in an airtight container. Yields about 1 1/2 cups.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay rolls flat on a cookie sheet.
Pinch edges together.
Bake as directed.
Cool completely.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Brown hamburger and onion, drain.
Mix all together but macaroni, pepperoni and part of the cheese.
Layer macaroni and sauce in dish like lasagna.
Put pepperoni and rest of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: hot crab pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Split muffins and butter. Spread mixture on muffins.
Cut each muffin into fourths.
Cut each fourth in half.
Broil until hot and bubbly.
May be frozen. Partly thaw when ready to serve.

title: nut snacks
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add other ingredients (only mix so as to leave some flour not completely blended in).
Spread dough in 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased) and pat down.

title: frozen pecan log roll
directions: Crumble real fine the wafers.
Mix Eagle Brand milk, then nuts, cherries and coconut; on wax paper, roll into long log in wax paper, then freeze.
Also very good without coconut and cherries.
A rich snack.

title: calypso pie
directions: Pour cookies into bowl and blend with softened butter with a pastry blender or a fork.
Place into a 10-inch pie pan and press crumb mixture firmly and evenly to bottom and sides of pan with the back of a spoon.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in small strips and brown in oil, turning often. Stir in onion soup mix and 2 cups water.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in peppers; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with 1/2 cup water.
Stir into meat mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Serve with cooked rice or mashed potatoes.

title: homemade french dressing
directions: Mix all in blender and keep
in refrigerator.
Makes 1 quart. This is very good and inexpensive.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Cook brownie mix according to package directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When done, punch holes in the brownies.
Mix 3 tablespoons coffee that has been perked and 1 tablespoon sugar. Drizzle into the brownies.
Mix 3 packages chocolate mousse according to directions.
Crumble up brownies in bottom of trifle bowl.
Over this put the mousse, then 12 ounces Cool Whip.
Fill to the top.
Break up 6 Skor candy bars and sprinkle on top.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in ungreased casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips; bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato loaf cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and water.
Beat on medium speed until mixture is well-blended.

title: 5 can casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Corning Ware dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Combine eggs, muffin mix, both corns, sour cream and butter. Spread in a 11 x 7 x 1-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes more or until knife comes out clean.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter and butter together with confectioners sugar until smooth texture develops.
Form small balls the size of buckeyes.
Refrigerate balls.
Next, melt slowly the chocolate chips and paraffin together in top of double boiler.
Using a toothpick, dip cold buckeyes into chocolate until 2/3 covered. Let dry on waxed paper.
Makes about 166 candies.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in long, narrow strips.
Salt, pepper and flour steak.
Brown in small amount of oil.
Drain oil and add tomatoes, onions and peppers.
Cook until tender, about 40 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: company cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions, adding mandarin oranges (drained).
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.
Cool.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Place raw berries in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and butter together with pastry blender.
Sprinkle over berries.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Delicious warm.
Some people like whipped cream or ice cream served over the crisp.

title: crispy fried chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Sprinkle in Accent and let stand 15 minutes.
Pour milk into bowl.
Combine flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces in milk; roll in flour mixture.
Pour oil in skillet to a depth of 1/2-inch.
Heat until a drop of water sizzles in oil.
Fry chicken, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes on each side, turning only once.
Drain well on absorbent paper.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a rolling boil.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring.
Then remove from heat.
Stir in 1 cup peanut butter. Blend in vanilla and oats.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken soup, mushroom soup, sour cream and water chestnuts; mix well and add chicken.
Put in a casserole dish and make a topping of 1 1/2 cup any butter cracker crumbs and 1 stick oleo.
Spread on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix and shape into balls, roll in chopped pecans and top with drained red cherries (freeze well).

title: bar-be-que beans
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper in skillet.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: lenora's ice cream
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Add enough carton milk to make 1 gallon.

title: easy and quick cucumber pickles
directions: Wash
cucumbers and slice into large pot.
Cover sliced cucumbers with
water,
add lime; stir, cover and let stand 24 hours.
Rinse
cucumbers until water is completely clear.
Mix together sugar, vinegar and spices; heat until hot.
Pour over drained cucumbers
and let stand 24 hours.	Cook cucumbers and sugar mixture 1 hour.
Pour into hot sterile jars.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, powdered sugar and melted butter. Spread in a 9 x 13 inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix together cream cheese, 1 c. powdered sugar, egg and Cool Whip.
Spread on pretzel mixture and chill while you dissolve jell-o in boiling water.
Add raspberries and pour on top of cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until set.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together salad oil, sugar and eggs.
Add zucchini, flour, cinnamon, vanilla, salt, baking soda and baking powder. Pour into 2 standard loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in greased pans.

title: country-style pork chops
directions: Place pork chops between 2 sheets of plastic wrap.
Pound lightly with flat side of mallet, until meaty portion covers about twice the surface as before pounding.
Sprinkle on both sides with salt and pepper.
Dip in flour to coat.
Beat together egg and water.
Dip chops into mixture.
Spread dry crumbs over plastic wrap and coat chops on both sides.
Lightly pound again to make crumbs adhere to chops.
Heat oil and butter in heavy skillet.
Add chops.
Cook over medium-high heat for 3 to 4 minutes on each side, until golden brown.
Transfer to heated platter.
Serve immediately.

title: ada's sweet potato pie
directions: Boil
sweet potatoes.
When done put through a sieve or mash thoroughly	with
masher.
Then add rest of ingredients. Pour into unbaked
pie
crust.
Bake	20 minutes in 425° oven. Reduce temperature
Continue baking 25 to 30 minutes longer or until knife comes out clean.

title: mom's fudge cake
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients and cool.
Sift together soda, salt, sugar and flour three times.
Add dry ingredients to chocolate mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Add eggs, sour milk and vanilla to chocolate mixture.
Stir well but don't overbeat.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or two 8-inch round pans.
Frost with Peanut Butter Fudge Frosting.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain well.
Add other ingredients.
Add salt to taste and mix well.
Fold in enough mayonnaise to hold ingredients together.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Cream shortening and sugar in large bowl.
Mix bananas, vanilla and eggs into mixture of shortening and sugar.
Sift flour, salt and soda; add alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in pecans and put into prepared pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Glaze is optional.

title: lite bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Yields approximately 15 muffins.

title: margarita jelly
directions: Measure water, lime juice, tequila and liqueur into a 6 or 8-quart saucepan.
Stir in food coloring.
Measure sugar into a separate bowl.
Mix sugar thoroughly into juice mixture.
Add margarine.
Bring to a full, rolling boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
Quickly stir in pectin.
Return to full rolling boil exactly 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; skin off any foam with metal spoon.
Ladle quickly into clean, hot jars filling to within 1/8-inch of top.
Wipe jar rims and threads. Cover with lids.
Screw bands tightly.
Invert jars 5 minutes, then turn upright.
Check seals after jars are cooled.
Makes about 5 (1 cup) jars.

title: brunch pizza
directions: Separate dough into triangles and put on 12-inch pizza pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Make 1/2-inch rim all around edges.
Beat eggs with seasoning and salt.
Pour onto crust.
Top with ham, cheese, broccoli, mushrooms, green pepper and tomato.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until eggs are set and crust is golden brown.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Put cucumbers, onion and green pepper in large airtight container.
Mix salt, vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed together and pour over cucumbers. Set in refrigerator and stir every day for three days or longer if needed.
Will keep several weeks.
Must be kept refrigerated.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix flour and margarine. Press mixture into bottom of an 11 x 7-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: baked potato in blanket
directions: Tenderize steak.
Peel potatoes. Rub salt on potatoes.
Cut steak into pieces to fit around potatoes.
Wrap and pin with toothpicks.
Roll in flour and brown in fat.
Place in greased casserole dish and bake in slow oven (325°) for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
May baste with hot water during baking to prevent steak from drying.
Good with brown gravy.

title: oven stew
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and cover.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Add potatoes, green peppers, salt and pepper one-half hour before serving.
Cook 7 hours for a double recipe.

title: cocktail wieners or smoked sausage
directions: Mix mustard and jelly in chafing dish or saucepan over low heat. Slice the frankfurters or sausage diagonally in bite size pieces. Add to sauce and heat through. Serve hot.

title: hard pretzels
directions: Spread butter over pretzels; sprinkle on soup mix and garlic powder.
Bake at 225° for 15 minutes on each side.

title: fruit salad cake
directions: Mix everything and bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: corn on the grill
directions: Pull back husks from corn.
(Do not remove.)
Remove silks. Rub corn with butter; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pull husks over corn and tie the top with heavy string.
Cook, covered with grill lid, over medium-hot coals (350° to 400°) for 15 to 20 minutes, turning occasionally.
Remove strings and serve.

title: grandma devrie's cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add orange juice and cranberry sauce.
Stir in ice cream.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter, add eggs and pecans.
Bake in shell 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit tea punch
directions: Make a syrup of sugar and water in a large saucepan.
Add tea, fruit juice and water (enough to make 1 1/2 gallons).
Add ginger ale just before serving.
May freeze all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Serves 50.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup and butter. Then stir in pecans and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in center of oven for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: roasted mustard potatoes
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Spray a roasting pan 3 times to coat with the vegetable oil.
Put the mustard, paprika, cumin, chili powder and cayenne pepper in a large bowl.
Whisk to blend. Prick the potatoes several times with the tines of a fork and add them to the bowl.
Toss to coat the potatoes evenly.
Pour the coated potatoes into the prepared roasting pan, leaving a little space between them.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until the potatoes are fork tender.

title: quick spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger and onion soup mix together.
Add sauce to hamburger and simmer 15 minutes.
Add to spaghetti or serve over spaghetti.

title: pepper steak(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: In a large skillet or wok, stir-fry the garlic in 1 tablespoon of the butter or margarine for 1 minute.
Add the onions and green sweet peppers; stir-fry for 4 to 5 minutes or until the vegetables are tender.
Transfer the vegetables with a slotted spoon to a bowl.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Gradually beat in egg yolks.
Blend in vanilla and pineapple.
Fold in sifted, dry ingredients.
Rinse beaters and beat egg whites.
Beat until stiff; fold into batter.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) cake pans, greased.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes.
Cool in pans for 5 minutes.
Frost with 7 Minute Icing.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Add salt and pepper to bread crumbs.
Beat eggs; add milk. Dip pork chops in liquid; roll in crumbs.
Put 3 tablespoons margarine in skillet; brown pork chops.
Place chops into a baking pan or dish; add boiling water.
Cover; bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
Take the cover off about the last 10 minutes.

title: leche frita(fried custard squares)
directions: Start preparation the night before or several hours in advance. In saucepan combine milk, lemon peel and cinnamon.
Bring to boil. Lower heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Set aside.
In another large saucepan, beat egg yolks until lemon colored.
Beat in 6 tablespoons sugar, then cornstarch.
Stir in few tablespoons of hot milk, then gradually stir in the rest.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, about 4 minutes or until thickened.
Discard lemon peel and cinnamon stick.
Pour into a large greased, rectangular pan and cool.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Cut into small squares.
Dust with flour and dip in beaten egg. Heat oil and fry until brown on all sides.
Drain.
Dust with a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Just before serving, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
If you wish, serve with strawberry jam.

title: double chocolate cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crushed cookies and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: onion soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion and saute 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Add broth, salt and pepper and bring to a boil.
Place bread in bottom of ovenproof casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of cheese.
Pour soup over bread and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake in 400° oven for 35 minutes.

title: oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat brown sugar, peanut butter and margarine until light and fluffy; blend in water, egg and vanilla. Add oats, flour and soda; mix well.
Chill dough until firm (about 30 minutes).
Form dough into 1-inch balls; place on ungreased cookie sheets and flatten slightly with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: taco dip and chips
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, sour cream and taco mix. Sprinkle
Mozzarella
and
Cheddar cheeses on top.	Serve with taco chips.

title: famous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter with both sugars.
Combine eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Add flour, oatmeal, salt, soda, and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add
grated chocolate, chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix well. Roll dough into balls and place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 6 - 7 minutes, until light brown.
Cool for 2 - 3 minutes and remove to rack to cool completely.
Yields approximately 10 dozen cookies.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt peanut butter in 2 sticks of butter or margarine.
Stir in the box of confectioners sugar.
Stir until well mixed.
Form into balls.
Put on waxed paper on a cookie sheet.
Place the balls in the refrigerator until chilled and firm.
Melt the chocolate chips and the paraffin.
When the balls are chilled, using toothpicks, dip each in the chocolate mixture and place in the refrigerator to set chocolate.
Can be frozen.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Add remaining ingredients (except spaghetti).
Cook over low heat until sauce is smooth and cheese is melted.
Add spaghetti and a little more broth.
Pour mixture into 2 medium casserole dishes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana bread pudding
directions: Place the bread cubes in a greased 2-quart casserole; pour butter over and toss to coat.
In a medium bowl, lightly beat eggs.
Add milk, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Stir in bananas.
Pour over bread cubes and stir to coat.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine and shortening.
Beat in 6 eggs.
Add flour, milk, vanilla and lemon juice; beat thoroughly. Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Start in cold oven and bake 1 3/4 hours at 350° until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chicken broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Combine both soups, water and pepper in bowl. Add to cooked chicken in frying pan; bring to boil. Stir in rice. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes. Add broccoli and peppers; simmer for 5 minutes uncovered.

title: steak and rice
directions: Cut steak in 1-inch cubes; brown in butter.
Add tomatoes, soy sauce, parsley, mushrooms, black pepper, water and bouillon cubes. Cook until steak is tender and broth is thickened.
Then add green pepper and onion.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: quick, healthy and easy chili beans
directions: Brown
meat
with
tablespoons
low-fat cooking oil. Drain. Put
meat in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on slow all day for a delicious home cooked dinner.

title: corn bread taco bake
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in next 5 ingredients; pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Prepare corn muffin mix except add 1/2 can onion rings.
Spoon around outer edge of casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes. Top with cheese and remaining onions.
Bake 2 or 3 minutes longer.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all, except onion rings.
Pour into baking dish.
Cover and bake 35 minutes at 375°.
Uncover and top with onion rings. Brown about five minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans, chop onion and combine with soups, bean sprouts and water chestnuts.
Add a shake of soy sauce.
Put in greased 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Combine soups and spread on top.
Grate cheese on top.
Heat in 350° oven until bubbly.
Top with fried onion rings and serve.

title: never fail chocolate icing
directions: Mix sugar and chocolate over low heat, add other ingredients. Bring mixture to a rapid boil.
Boil one minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool.
Spread on cake.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs, oil, bananas, nuts and pineapple.
Grease and flour 3 layer cake pans. Pour into the 3 pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Frost.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Lay asparagus in casserole dish with eggs sliced on top; set aside.
Make cheese sauce in pan.
Heat milk, butter and flour, then add cheese and mix until smooth.
Pour over asparagus and eggs.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Mix yeast, water and sugar until dissolved.
Mix in all other ingredients until well mixed.
Let rise, punch down and make into rolls.
Place on lightly oiled pan and let rise again.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: fudge
directions: Stir good; put on low heat until melted.
Let boil 7 minutes, add 3 six-ounce packages of chocolate chips, 1 pint marshmallow creme and 1 1/2 cup nuts.
Let cool short time and pour into large cookie sheets.
Makes 4 lb.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together in casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: diabetic cookies(1 serving bread)
directions: Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cream together butter and powdered sugar. Add in flour and blend thoroughly. Press into ungreased 9 x 13 baking pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Combine eggs, sugar and lemon juice and blend until light lemony color. Add dry ingredients together and add to lemon mixture. Pour into baked crust for 30 minutes. Cool and sift a little powdered sugar over top. Cut into squares and serve.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large saucepan.
Add onions, carrots and peppers.
Cook until onions and carrots are tender. Add beef; cook until crumbly.
Stir in juice, potatoes and seasonings.
Cover and cook over low heat for 25 minutes.
Mix flour with 1 cup of milk; beat until free of lumps.
Add to soup. Add rest of milk.
Heat and serve.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cut up all vegetables into bite size pieces.
Add the rest of ingredients and simmer over low heat for 1 hour.

title: frosty holiday grapes
directions: Combine sugar and gelatin; mix well.
Dip grape clusters in water; shake off excess water.
Sprinkle sugar mixture through a sieve over wet grapes.
Place on waxed paper about 45 minutes or until completely dry.
Makes 10 edible garnishes.
(Very decorative from Thanksgiving through the New Year; makes your table and platters very attractive.)

title: nutty nuggets
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add all other ingredients except powdered sugar.
Stir until mixed well.
Form little balls and bake 15 minutes at 350 degrees.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar. Makes about 48 balls.

title: no-fuss lasagna
directions: To make a day ahead and bake just before serving:
In a large saucepan, brown ground beef; drain.
Add tomato paste, water, spaghetti sauce mix, sugar, parsley, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Simmer, partially covered, for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: cajun dirty rice
directions: In a large skillet, brown pork and gizzards in hot oil.
Add flour, onion, green pepper, celery, garlic, parsley, salt and spices.
Simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: To make sauce, cook onion in butter or margarine until tender, but not brown.
Stir in flour, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.

title: wassail
directions: Boil together in pan.

title: piggy bank pork bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles as directed on package. Drain.
Melt shortening in large skillet. Brown meat.
Drain off fat. Stir in noodles, soup, corn (with liquid), pimiento (with liquid), cheese and green pepper.
Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes, stirring occasionally. Makes 6 servings.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by spoon into hot deep fat.
Cook until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot.

title: dream salad
directions: Combine jello, sugar and pineapple juice in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows that have been cut into small pieces.
Cool.
Drain pineapple.
Add the remaining ingredients to jello mixture.
Whip the whipping cream first.
I use long square glass dish.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours.

title: anytime muffins
directions: Mix together cereal, flour, salt, baking soda and sugar. Add eggs, oil and buttermilk; stir well. Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 5 dozen muffins.

title: oven fish chowder
directions: Put ingredients in large casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Scald cream and add when done.

title: anna's favorite casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain fat.
Put hamburger into casserole dish.
Spread drained corn on top of meat.
Make potatoes according to package directions.
Spread on top of corn.
Sprinkle cheese over the top of the potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes to heat and melt cheese.

title: potato biscuits
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets on; take them out of skimmer; drain and squeeze with a towel to insure being dry.
Remove the skin; mash perfectly free from lumps.
Add butter, egg and sweet milk. When cool, beat in yeast.
Put in just enough flour to make stiff dough.
When this rises, do the same as biscuits and bake.
Dough can be dropped into meat soups for pot pie.

title: divinity
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, and water in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved; cook without stirring to 260° (a little dropped into cold water forms a hard ball).
Remove from heat and pour, beating constantly in a fine stream into the beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla and continue beating until mixture holds its shape and becomes slightly dull; fold in nuts.
Drop quickly from tip of buttered spoon onto waxed paper in individual peaks or spread in butter pan and cut into 1-inch squares when firm.
Makes 48 squares.

title: homemade finger paint
directions: Mix flour with salt.
Add 2 1/2 cups cold water.
Stir until smooth.
Gradually add this mixture to 2 cups boiling water.
Boil until smooth.
Add food coloring and stir until well blended.

title: shrimp creole(for 4)
directions: Melt 2 teaspoons margarine in a heavy saucepan and add celery, onion and green pepper.
Saute until onions are clear.
Add tomatoes and seasonings and simmer 20 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook for 3 minutes or until shrimp turns pink.
Sprinkle with parsley. Serve on rice.

title: krispy bars
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in peanut butter, blending well. Remove from heat and spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour Rice Krispies over peanut butter mixture in pan and press firmly. Melt remaining ingredients in saucepan and pour over Rice Krispies.
Cut into bars.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: old-fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Cook pumpkin and combine with eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in sugar and
flour.
Blend
in spices and milk.
Mix thoroughly. Pour into already baked pie shells.
Makes 3 to 4 pies.
Bake until golden brown.

title: chicken a la maria elena
directions: Hint:
For less fat, mix 1/2 Total 1% with regular.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients; beat until fluffy.
Beat in flour with flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: hearty macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and cool thoroughly.
In a large mixing bowl, combine crabmeat, eggs, celery, onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
Combine with macaroni and chill before serving.
Garnish with additional hard-cooked eggs.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Layer
pineapple and bread crumbs.
Top with butter and sugar. Bake about 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Delicious with ham.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients first, then put the eggs and milk in mixing bowl and stir along with molasses.
Pour this in the dry ingredients; mix like you would biscuits, until it is all thoroughly mixed.
Pinch off a piece of dough and put in about 7 or 8-inch pie pan; roll this on a floured board or your table.
Cut with a biscuit cutter or even something larger for bigger cookies. Bake at 350° for about 12 or 13 minutes.
Stick toothpick in the cookies or cake to see if it comes out dry, if so, it's done.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Place berries in bottom
of 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Mix dry ingredients in bowl; add melted butter, milk and beaten eggs. Spoon batter over berries.
Mix an additional 1/3 c. sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cornstarch.
Sprinkle over batter.
Now, pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken in barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large skillet until tender. Add remaining ingredients, except chicken, and simmer 5 minutes. Add the chicken and cover with lid. Cook over medium heat for 45 minutes, turning once.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Melt oleo and add flour, spinach juice, milk and onion.
Cook until thick.
Add seasonings and cheese.
Stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Add spinach.
Set in the refrigerator 6 hours or overnight.
Bake uncovered 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl; beat until well blended.
Add egg; beat until just blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.	Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Saute onion in butter; add to broccoli.
Stir in rice.
Add Cheez Whiz and mushroom soup.
Put in large shallow dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at
350° until bubbly.

title: baked grapefruit with raisins and nuts
directions: Cut grapefruit in half crosswise.
Run knife around each segment to loosen.
Snip out the center core with kitchen shears. Combine raisins and walnuts; place in center of each grapefruit half.
Drizzle honey over grapefruit.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes or until heated through.
Serve at once.
Yields 4 servings.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: You will need 1 large brown bag.

title: mrs. h. s. avant, sr. cucumber pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; cut in pieces.
Place in dish; cover with boiling water.
Sprinkle salt and alum over cucumbers.
Let cucumbers stand in water until water is lukewarm.
Remove from water and rinse.
Drain on towel.
Make syrup of sugar, vinegar and spices.
Boil syrup; pour over cucumbers which have been placed in sterilized jars.
Seal and turn upside down.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Bake in a greased loaf pan in a preheated 350° oven 80 minutes for metal loaf pan or 65 minutes for glass loaf pan.

title: marjorie's chicken
directions: Mix all together and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered, or until chicken is tender.
Serve with white rice.

title: christmas tree sandwiches
directions: You will need a Christmas tree cookie cutter; be sure cutter is not larger than bread.

title: crunchy pound cake
directions: Mix shortening and sugar thoroughly; add eggs, alternating with flour.
Add flavorings.
Bake in a tube pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and let cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni. Toss in oil. Mix remaining ingredients and add to lightly greased crock-pot. Cover and cook on low 3 to 4 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt oleo.
Combine with flour to make a paste.
Combine cottage cheese and eggs; add to flour mixture.
Add cheese to broccoli.
Put in a buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chops
directions: In a large skillet, brown pork chops in oil; sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper.
Meanwhile, in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish, combine rice, water, tomato sauce and taco seasoning; mix well.
Arrange chops over rice; top with green pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until chops are browned and juices run clear.
Uncover and sprinkle with cheese; bake until cheese is melted.

title: diabetic fluffy fruit dessert
directions: Mix and chill thoroughly.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pour hot vinegar back over pickles and seal.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook meat, onion and garlic until brown.
Add tomatoes, paste, pepper, salt, oregano and basil.
Cook 15 minutes.

title: fluffy coconut frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in sugar, milk and extract.
Fold in whipped topping and coconut.
Makes about 4 cups or enough to frost tops and sides of 2 (8 or 9-inch) cakes.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Saute
pumpkin and sugar in butter over medium heat for 15 minutes.
Add
milk,
salt	and
pepper.
Bring to a boil. Serve with toast on crackers.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients until fluffy.
Add rest of ingredients.
Roll about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter. Bake in 425° oven, about 12 minutes, or light brown.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well; add beaten whole egg.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with the soup.
Add chopped nuts and dates, which have been floured lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and frost.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Heat to boil the apple juice, cloves and lemon juice.
In a mug, place the cinnamon stick, butter and rum.
After removing the cloves, pour the hot juice into the prepared mug.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Cook sugar, crushed pineapple and jello in pan until dissolved.
Add 2 cups cool water.
Set until about half set and add cream cheese and Velveeta cheese.
Stir and then fold Cool Whip into it and let set several hours.

title: caramel cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions substituting the buttermilk for the water and adding the pudding.
Bake in layer pans.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Set aside. Saute onions in butter.
Add noodles and cook uncovered 3 minutes. Stir in broccoli (including liquid) and pepper.
Cook 3 more minutes.
Add milk and cheese and stir until cheese melts.

title: misti's ice cream
directions: *Use 4 bananas (crushed), 2 cups strawberries, 2 cups peaches or 1 small container of Hershey's chocolate syrup.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in one bowl.
Pour into greased loaf pans and bake one hour at 325°.

title: texas monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle chopped pecans in the bottom of well-greased 10-inch Bundt pan; set aside.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into quarters and roll each piece in sugar mixture.
Layer in pan. Combine brown sugar and butter.
Pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan and invert.

title: italian tomato sauce
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil.
Add pepper and onion.
Add meat; saute.
Add crushed tomatoes and paste.
Add spices; add water. Simmer on low for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve over favorite pasta.
May substitute boneless pork for pepperoni or hamburg.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Mix well and congeal.

title: cajun stewed okra
directions: Soak okra in cold water about 30 minutes before cooking.
Drain and cut into pieces.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, garlic powder and season all.
Drop okra into a bag into which you have placed the flour.
Shake bag coating the okra.
In large skillet covered with oil and heated, drop okra in and fry until slime is gone.
Add all dry ingredients while stirring over low heat to keep from sticking. When okra is tender add all other ingredients cover and cook over low heat adding water as needed to keep from sticking.
Stir often. You may add more salt, pepper, etc, to reach flavor desired. Should cook at least 1 hour.

title: aunt marie's pickles
directions: Dissolve salt, mustard seed, celery seed and sugar in vinegar over low heat.
Do not boil!
Cool and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Will keep in refrigerator for months or can be frozen.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil until clear over moderate heat.
Add jello (dry).
Put strawberries in mixture and pour in baked pie shell.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip when ready to serve.

title: oatmeal-coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir all filling ingredients in a large bowl until well blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes, until top and crust are golden and a pick inserted in center comes out clean but oily (filling may still jiggle in center).
Serves 8.

title: phat-thai
directions: Soak the
rice stick (like noodles) in warm water until tender, but
not
soft.
In
a
large wok, saute garlic in hot oil, add
shrimp and cook until just pink.	Remove shrimp, set it aside
and	add
chicken.
Remove chicken after browned and cook the
eggs, scrambled, chopping the eggs with spatula when firm. Remove
the
eggs
and stir-fry the tofu.
Remove tofu, add noodles,
vinegar,	paprika
and
cayenne
pepper
sauce; cook for
minutes, stirring constantly.
Mix in previously cooked ingredients
and bean sprouts.
Toss well and cook for an additional 3 to 4 minutes.	Serve with a topping of crushed peanuts and (optional) lemon wedges on the side.

title: pecan squares
directions: Beat egg whites in bowl, add sugar and melted butter.
Add vanilla, nuts and flour.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cut into squares when cool.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Soften bread crumbs in milk.
Add beef, onions, eggs and seasoning.
Brown in butter.
Remove meat balls.
Stir in flour. Blend well.
Dissolve cubes in hot water.
Add to flour.
Add milk and cream.
Cook.
Stir constantly until smooth (3 minutes).
Add meat balls.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes until sauce is desired consistency.
Makes 96 (1-inch) meat balls.

title: stuffed okra curry
directions: Mix all the spices and salt together; set aside.
Slit the okra lengthwise without separating all the way through.
Stuff them individually with spice mixture.
Heat up oil in a vessel. When hot, add stuffed okra.
Saute it for a few minutes, then cover the vessel with a lid and let cook on medium heat.
Stir the okra intermittently to prevent burning.
May add more oil if needed.
Cook the okra until done.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Add salt and soak 3 hours in ice water. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and seal in jars.

title: pop cake
directions: Add can of pop ONLY to the cake mix and mix and bake according to the directions on the box.
DO NOT ADD OIL, WATER OR EGGS.

title: rice medley
directions: Saute onion, peppers and mushrooms in half stick of margarine. Boil rice, add onion, pepper and mushrooms to rice, add corn and other half stick of margarine.
Season with salt and pepper and place in microwave to heat.
You can also make it a main dish by adding fried scallops or chunked chicken.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Mix the cake mix according to directions and bake until done in layers.
Cool and frost with Icing.
Beat eggs.
Add milk, sugar and margarine.
Cook over medium heat for about 12 minutes, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and add coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Spread on cooled cake layers.

title: the big bad wolf's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with margarine.
Melt the margarine and chocolate in a large saucepan over very low heat.
Remove the saucepan from the heat. Stir in the sugar, flour, baking powder, vanilla and eggs and beat well with an eggbeater.
Stir in nuts.

title: sweet potato crisp
directions: Cook sweet potatoes; peel and slice crosswise, about 3/8-inch thick.
Spread in a greased shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cut margarine into flour and brown sugar as you would in making a pie crust.
Add pepper, milk and ground nuts; mix well.
Spread over potato slices.
Broil about 6-inches from heat until bubbly and carmelized, about 7 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into 1-inch balls.
Store in covered container in refrigerator or freezer.
When ready to use, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
These are not baked.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in salt water (enough salt in the water to float an egg).
Let stand 30 minutes to 1 hour; drain.
Pack in jars with dill weed, hot peppers and garlic to your liking.
Heat water, salt, vinegar and sugar.
Pour one cup over cucumbers and seal.
Let set for 6 weeks.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour, salt and cocoa 3 times and add alternately to creamed mixture with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and red coloring. Last fold in soda and vinegar; do not beat.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Microwave on High for 2 minutes the chocolate and butter. Stir in milk and add sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add vanilla.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil chicken until done.
Cut up into bite-size pieces.
Mix cream of chicken soup with milk. Cook noodles, following directions on package.
Drain.
In a casserole dish, layer noodles, chicken and soup mixture, then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: honey roasted apples
directions: Pare top 1/3 of apples and remove core, leaving 1/2-inch of core on bottom.
Place apples in oiled baking dish.

title: virginia carrot pineapple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients until moistened. Bake in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.
May use a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan or a 10 x 2-inch round pan. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting when cooled.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Combine peas, peppers, cucumber and scallions in medium bowl. Combine remaining ingredients (except lettuce) in a 2 cup glass measure; whisk until thoroughly blended.
Pour over peas; toss well.
Arrange lettuce on platter; serve salad on top.
Keeps well for several hours at room temperature.
Refrigeration is not advised as it hardens the peas.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together; mixer may be used.
Grease pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mamie's squash supreme
directions: Drain
squash; stir in onion, soup, sour cream, carrot, cheese,
salt
and
pepper.
Sprinkle layer of stuffing mix in buttered
casserole.
Add
squash mixture; cover with layer of stuffing
mix.
Dot generously with butter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes or put in microwave for 15 minutes at Medium-high until heated through.

title: lynn wear's winter apple conserve
directions: Wash, core and chop apples.
Chop raisins, orange peel and ginger.
Add rest of ingredients, except walnuts.
Start at low heat and when sugar is dissolved, let mix boil gently about 30 minutes.
Stir often.
Add walnuts.
Pour into 1/2-pint canning jars.
Seal and process 15 minutes in water bath.
Serve as condiment or use as mincemeat by adding butter and brandy for tarts, pies or pudding.
Makes about 5 half pints.

title: peanut buddy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: tea cakes(grandma baden's recipe)
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and eggs together.
Add vanilla and buttermilk.
Stir in flour with baking powder and salt.
Mixture will be soft.
Drop by spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: cheddar casserole
