directions: In a small skillet, melt 2 tablespoons margarine over moderate heat.
When foam subsides, add the onion and cook 4 or 5 minutes until translucent but not brown.
Bring 2 cups water to boil in 1 quart pan.
Add salt and slowly pour in grits, without allowing water to stop boiling.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to medium and cook 2 minutes.
Add the onions, Worcestershire and Tabasco, a little black pepper and 1 1/2 cups grated Cheddar combined with 3 tablespoons soft butter.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and onion; strain.
Let water stand until starch settles.
Pour off water, keeping starch.
Add starch to potatoes.
Add all other ingredients except oil.
Heat oil in frying pan.
Brown pancakes well on each side.
Drain on paper towels and serve.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: apple-beef casserole(dietetic)
directions: Brown beef and drain thoroughly.
Combine beef, apple, onion and sauerkraut and place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with tomato juice and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: rice-sausage dressing
directions: Soak bread cubes in warm milk.
Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Mix all ingredients.
Use to stuff turkey.

title: praline bars
directions: Spray cookie sheet with Pam spray.
Place cookies in single layer on cookie sheet.
Melt margarine.
Add brown sugar and nuts. Bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Spread mixture over crackers.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Cut or break into pieces.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan. Refrigerate 12 hours and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until set and brown (uncovered).

title: watermelon slices
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water in medium bowl. Stir in cold water.
Pour into 8-inch round cake pan.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add 2 cups of flour and beat until smooth.
Add corn syrup, butter and salt.
Mix well for 2 minutes. Add remaining flour and knead until all flour is worked into dough.
Cover and put in warm place until dough doubles in size (1 to 1 1/2 hours)*.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: Add salt to Jell-O; drain pineapple and add enough water to make 3 1/2 cups.
Heat.
Mix in Jell-O and cool until slightly thickened.
Fold in softened cream cheese and beat with mixer at high speed for a few minutes.
Add pineapple and beat until cheese is smooth.
Add nuts and celery.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for a few hours until solid.

title: oatmeal dinner rolls
directions: Combine oatmeal and buttermilk; set aside for 5 minutes.
Add eggs and sugar; mix well.
Mix together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Stir all together adding oil last.
Fill muffin pans half full and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Excellent with honey butter.

title: biscuits supreme
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in margarine.
Add milk. Mix in quickly.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Knead gently 1/2 minute.
Roll to 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Cut and bake at 450° on ungreased sheet 10 to 12 minutes.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix and press in oblong pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°. Cool in refrigerator.

title: frozen fruit punch
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Add orange juice and water, lemonade and water and pineapple juice.
When cool, add bananas.
Freeze. Two hours prior to serving, remove from freezer.
Add 2 (28 ounce) bottles ginger ale at table.

title: chicken baked pork chops
directions: Using a flameproof ovenproof casserole, brown the salted chops in drippings.
Cover with rice.
Combine soup and milk; pour over rice, making sure all rice is moistened.
Cover tightly.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter yummies
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Roll each in peanuts.
Chill 4 or 5 hours.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: gingered fruit
directions: If you are using dried figs, place them in a bowl and pour boiling water over them.
Let stand 10 minutes, then drain and cut in half lengthwise.
Cut fresh figs in half lengthwise, unless they are very small.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Arrange one-third of sliced cake on the bottom of a trifle dish or large decorative bowl.
Prepare pudding according to package directions. Place one-third more cake pieces around inside of bowl, using half of pudding to hold them in place.
Gently stir together jam and strawberries. Spoon half over pudding.
Cover with remaining cake pieces.
Layer remaining pudding and strawberry mixture.
Chill.
Garnish with whipped cream and fresh strawberries.

title: pudding popsicles(great for kids!)
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions and pour into small paper cups.
Insert wooden (popsicle) sticks or plastic spoons.
Freeze for 3 hours or until firm.
Peel off paper cups and enjoy!

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Using 1/2 of all the ingredients, you're going to make two exact layers.

In a 2-quart baking dish, begin layering on the bottom with Tater Tots, soup, onion, ham and ending with cheese. Repeat exactly in the same order with the other 1/2 of the ingredients, ending with cheese on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° or until cheese is melted.

title: guacamole
directions: Put everything in a bowl; mix well with fork; ready to serve.

title: macaroni hamburger casserole
directions: Cook meat; drain. Add soup and onion. Simmer.
Mix macaroni with meat mixture and place in casserole dish.
Cover with cheese and place under broiler until melted.
Serve hot.

title: granny's easy biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Shape dough into biscuits and place in a greased pan. Bake in 450° oven until done.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk, soy sauce, pepper, green beans, and 2/3 c fried onions in a 1 1/2 qt casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot. Stir; sprinkle remaining onions on top. Bake 5 minutes longer or until bubbly.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in hot oil until tender.
Add water and bouillon cubes; dissolve.
Add noodles and salt.
Cover; boil for 3 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and garlic powder; cook 4 minutes.
Add cheese, milk and dash of pepper.
Cook until cheese is melted. Serves 8.

title: yummy sugar cookies
directions: Mix well roll in ball and flatten with glass dipped in sugar. Bake in 400 degrees until golden brown.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Blend together sugar, eggs and oil.
Add dry ingredients. Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes for layers or put in tube pan for 1 hour at 325° or until done when tested with toothpick.

title: perfect barbecue slaw
directions: Mix and season to taste.
Chill for a few hours.

title: aunt ola's seven in one
directions: Peel and slice potatoes thin.
Peel and slice carrots and onion.
Slice celery (dice).
Put all ingredients in a 2 1/2 to 3-quart cassserole dish with lid.
Bake until done, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.
Brown chop meat; drain and put on top of casserole.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes.
Cool slightly and grate while still warm.
Mix together the sour cream, celery soup, onions and melted butter.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Place into small baking dish.
Top with 1/2 cup chopped sauteed pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: potato pot pie
directions: Cook mushrooms and onion in 2 tablespoons dressing over medium-high
heat.	Add
flour
and seasonings.
Gradually add milk,
stirring
until thick.
Stir in 1 cup dressing, turkey, vegetables	and
1 cup cheese.
Cook 5 minutes.
Spoon mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Spread over cooled cake. If mixture is too stiff, add 1 to 4 teaspoons milk until it is smoother and easier to spread.
This icing is perfect for the Red Velvet Cake, Italian Cream Cake and Carrot Cake.

title: banana-pineapple spice cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add eggs.
Stir all dry ingredients together and add to egg mixture.
Add bananas and nuts.
Bake in three greased and floured 9-inch pans at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: turkey with wild rice(for leftover turkey)
directions: Wash wild rice thoroughly.
Drop into boiling water; add 1 teaspoon salt.
Cook 25 to 40 minutes.
Drain and rinse.
Heat 1/2 of the butter with onions and mushrooms until soft.
Use remaining half for the white sauce.

title: chocolate-malt cheesecake
directions: Stir ingredients well; pat in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: picante sauce
directions: Put ingredients in food processor.
Pour into large pot and cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Process in boiling water for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole (2)
directions: Mix together soup, mayo, lemon juice and cheese.
Mix bread crumbs and butter for top of casserole.
Mix all ingredients together and add sliced mushrooms.	Pour into casserole dish & top with bread crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Can be frozen.

title: crow's nest
directions: Cook apples down some, either on top of stove or in microwave. Add sugar and cinnamon, like you would for an apple pie.
Put in cake pan.
Cover apples with biscuit mix.
Bake at 350° until done.
Serve with a mix.

title: tutti frutti ice cream
directions: Combine fruit and juice.
Add sugar, eggs, vanilla and salt. Mix well.
Add milk and pour into freezer can.
Freeze.

title: butterscotch-oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Cream together shortening, brown sugar and sugar in bowl until light and fluffy.
Add egg; beat well. Stir dry ingredients into creamed mixture, blending well.
Add oats.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 3 inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from baking sheets when slightly cooled.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: orange balls
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Blend in orange juice.
Add crumbs.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Refrigerate until firm enough to serve.

title: banana bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Beat sugar, sour cream, margarine and egg whites in large bowl on low speed for 1 minute, scraping bowl occasionally.
Beat in bananas and vanilla on low speed for 30 seconds.
Beat in flour, salt and baking soda on medium speed for 1 minute, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown; cool.
Cut into 2 1/4 x 1 1/2-inch bars.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten whole eggs.
Add vanilla and vinegar.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Start baking at 300°; bake 10 minutes.
Raise temperature to 350°.
Complete baking time is about 45 minutes.
Real good!

title: kahlua mousse
directions: Chill medium bowl and beaters.
Combine cream and coffee powder in chilled bowl.
Beat until soft peaks form.
Add Kahlua and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
In small bowl beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add 2 teaspoons sugar; beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg white into whipped cream
mixture.
Transfer to dessert bowl, cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Decorate with chocolate curls.
Chill in a 1 1/2-quart souffle dish if desired.
Serves 4.

title: mexican bean casserole
directions: Brown onion and meat, drain.
Add meat mixture to soups, beans and sauce.
Bring mixture to boil.
Tear tortillas into strips and layer in casserole dish; then add meat mixture and strips of tortillas.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400 degrees.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken; take from bone and cut into bite size pieces. Drop tortillas into chicken broth until limp.
Line bottom of casserole dish with tortillas.
Add chicken in order, chili powder, the cream soup and tomatoes.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 2-quart dish at 325°, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crab casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add soup, milk, eggs, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Mix well.
Reserve enough cheese and cracker crumbs to cover top of casserole.
Add remaining cheese and crumbs to soup mixture with salt and crabmeat.
Put in buttered casserole; cover with reserved cheese and crumbs.
Place in a 325° oven until thoroughly heated and brown on top.

title: baked limas
directions: Cook beans in fresh water to which 1 teaspoon salt is added. Drain and rinse in hot water.
Pour into a flat baking dish.
Add and stir in margarine.

title: deep dish cheddar chicken and rice
directions: Saute onion in 1/4 cup margarine.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly,
until thickened.
Add chicken, cheese (2 cups), rice and broccoli.
Mix well.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add remaining 1 cup of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cookie bars
directions: Combine margarine, cake mix and 2 eggs in mixer bowl.
Mix well. Batter will be stiff.
Spoon into greased cake pan.
Beat cream cheese and confectioners sugar in mixer bowl until light. Beat in 2 eggs.
Mix in coconut and pecans.
Spread over cake batter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pistachio pudding fruit salad
directions: Mix dry pudding with fruit.
Add marshmallows; fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate, then serve.

title: egg salad
directions: Chop the eggs; mix all ingredients.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt butter in microwave.
Add corn syrup and brown sugar to melted butter.
Stir and cook in microwave oven for 3 minutes on High power.
Stir soda into butter mixture.
Stir vanilla into foamy butter mixture.
Mixture will become foamy.
Pour on popped corn.
Stir as you pour.

title: oven oxtail stew
directions: Place oxtails in roasting pan at about 375° for about 1 hour. Drain off excessive fat.
Have vegetables cut to your favorite size.
Place in pan with oxtails.
Pour in beef broth; season to taste.
Add 1 tablespoon cooking wine.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Return to oven and cook until oxtails are well done.
May or may not need to add small amount of water.
Serve as is or with rice.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in 9-inch pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour and baking powder; add milk and mix well.
Pour over oleo.
Do not stir. Pour cherries over batter.
Do not mix.
Sprinkle other 1/2 cup of sugar over batter.
Bake at 325° in preheated oven for 1 hour.

title: turkey chutney salad
directions: Measure 1/3 cup of chutney and drain the syrup into a large bowl.
Finely chop chutney pieces and combine with syrup.
Cut turkey into 1/2-inch cubes.
Add to bowl with mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper; mix until combined.
Divide salad among 4 individual serving plates lined with lettuce leaves.
Sprinkle each with chopped almonds and garnish with the artichoke hearts, cucumber and radishes, dividing evenly.
Serves 4.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook ground beef and diced onion until meat is done. Drain liquid off. Add drained mushrooms, salt, pepper, garlic powder and Kitchen Bouquet.
Stir in soup and heat thoroughly. Add sour cream right before serving. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: grape salad
directions: Wash and completely dry grapes. In a big bowl, mix sugar, cream cheese, sour cream, vanilla and desired amount of pecans. Mix well. Add grapes and mix it up. Sprinkle on top the brown sugar and the rest of the pecans.

title: quick and easy cheeseburger bake
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Add soup, vegetables and milk. Set aside.	Mix Bisquick and water and spread on bottom of greased 9 X 13 baking dish.
Pour hamburger mixture over bisquick mixture. Bake for 20 minutes at 400 degrees.
Top with cheese and return to over for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually
add
sugar.
Beat
in egg and almond extract (by
hand).
Gradually
blend
in flour.
Chill dough for ease in handling.
Roll out dough on lightly floured surface to 1/8
inch thickness.
(We like them thin;
however, you can make them
thicker,
if	so desired.) Cut into desired shapes and bake at	350°
on
ungreased cookie sheet (about 10 minutes, or	until golden
brown).
Frost
with confectioners sugar frosting when cool.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients well with electric beater.
Refrigerate.
Put on salad just before serving.
Spinach, mushrooms and hard-boiled eggs.

title: old fashioned marble pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Measure flour and sift together with baking powder and salt.
Set aside. In large mixing bowl, mix sugar and Crisco.
Beat until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla.
Add flour mix alternately with milk.
Take out 2 cups of batter and mix with cocoa.
Layer batter into tube pan beginning and ending with white batter.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Combine first
ingredients
to
make a sauce (do not dilute soups).
Cook
chicken
breasts
in salted water until done, then cut into pieces.
Cook broccoli just until tender. Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Place layer of broccoli, layer of chicken pieces and layer of sauce.
Repeat layers.
Cook at 375° until
bubbly.
Top
with
cheese
and cook until melted. Serves 6.

title: cranberry pork roast
directions: Place pork roast in slow cooker.
In a medium bowl, mash cranberry sauce; stir in sugar, cranberry juice, mustard and cloves.
Pour over roast.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or until tender.
Remove roast and keep warm.
Skim fat from juices.
Measure 2 cups, adding water if necessary and pour into saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Combine cornstarch and cold water to make a paste; stir into gravy.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Season with salt.
Serve with sliced pork.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked egg strata
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in croutons.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat 1 dozen eggs.
Add Carnation milk and enough regular milk to make 4 cups.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix all liquid together; pour over croutons and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight. In the morning, cook bacon; crumble over pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: abeliene beans and rice
directions: In saucepan, cook onion and green pepper with cumin in butter until tender.
Add broth, water, rice, salt and pepper.
Cover, bring to boil.
Reduce heat, simmer for 25 minutes or until done. Stir occasionally.
Add beans and pimento.
Heat.
Makes about 5 1/2 cups or 4 servings.

title: fried mozzarella
directions: Cut Mozzarella into 1/4 to 1/3-inch thick slices.
In a shallow bowl, combine bread crumbs and parsley.
In second bowl, beat the eggs with small amount water and add some salt and pepper.
Place flour in third shallow bowl.
Dip the cheese slices into flour until completely covered.
Dip floured cheese into egg mixture, then in bread crumbs, then repeat the egg and bread crumbs until sides and edges are covered.
Heat olive oil in 2 large skillets on medium.
Saute cheese slices until crispy and golden brown (a few minutes on each side; watch carefully). Remove from heat and drain on paper towel.
Serve immediately.

title: crab and mushroom dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart microwavable casserole dish with lid.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Cook another minute.
Stir.

title: slow-cooked barbecued beef
directions: Prepare this in a slow cooker before game time. Just throw in all the ingredients and let cook.
You can serve the meat by itself or on rolls.

title: mustard eggs
directions: Mix vinegar and yellow mustard; add sugar, salt, mustard seed, cloves, celery seed and a few drops food coloring; simmer, about 10 minutes.
Slice onions and pour juice over the onions when hot. Add eggs and refrigerate.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in skins until nearly tender.
Peel and halve.
Arrange
in
greased
shallow 1 quart baking pan. Combine sugar,
water, salt and butter; pour over sweet potatoes.
Bake in	moderate oven at 350° for 15 minutes, basting occasionally. Sprinkle
top
with
coconut;
bake
10 minutes longer or until lightly browned.

title: rhubarb sauce
directions: Place rhubarb pieces, water, sugar and food color in a pan. Cook slow until soft.
Then add strawberry jello and frozen strawberries.
Cook slow until strawberries thaw.

title: caldo con queso
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Add 1/2 cheese.
Heat. Serve with cheese on top.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, oleo and milk in a heavy 2 1/4-quart pan. Bring to a full, rolling boil while stirring constantly.
Continue boiling for 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat mixture until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares or desired shape.

title: cold broccoli salad
directions: Wash and trim off broccoli flowers from a large head of broccoli.
Add 1/2 pound of bacon, crumbled and fully cooked. Also cut the red onion into little rings or dice and add to other ingredients.
Add pecan chips (small) and raisins.

title: champagne or any booze punch
directions: Serve plain or add champagne or any booze.

title: chicken casserole deluxe
directions: Prepare noodle mix as directed on package, using 1/2 cup milk instead of 1/3.
Stir in other ingredients and pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbling hot.
Regular noodles and sour cream may be used in place of Romanoff mix.

title: sensational shrimp dip
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Serve with chips, crackers or vegetable dippers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: sausage bread
directions: Fry sausage and onion together until done. Drain well.
Spread bread dough on well greased cookie sheet until the dough is flat and covers the cookie sheet.
Mix eggs and cheese together.
Add the sausage and onion; mix well.
Spread evenly over the dough. Roll up like a jelly roll.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Let cool, then slice and eat.

title: 5 cup favorite salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients and refrigerate for 24 hours. If desired, top with cherries for color.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Roll into small balls.
At this point, the balls may be frozen to use at a later date.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve with toothpicks.
Makes 60 to 72 balls.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Make amounts according to amount of meat desired.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
When mixture begins to boil, time for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add next 4 ingredients; add flour last.
Mix and place on greased jelly roll pan.
Makes 3 pounds.
Delicious.

title: strawberry no-bake pie
directions: Add lemon juice to condensed milk a little at a time.
Add container of Cool Whip.
Add strawberries.
Put into graham cracker pie shell and refrigerate until set.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Mix and put in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan the flour, pecans and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown. Cool completely.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine crunch peanut butter, softened oleo, brown sugar (packed) and granulated sugar. Beat until creamy.
Gradually beat in eggs and vanilla.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend into peanut butter mixture.
Spread into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Place in 350° oven for 5 minutes. Remove from oven; run knife blade through to marbleize.
Return to oven; bake 25 minutes more.
Cool and cut into 2 x 1-inch bars. Makes 4 dozen.

title: sheppard's pie
directions: Cook ground beef, onions and celery in large skillet until meat is browned and drain excess grease.
Add soup and stir.
Add thyme.
Spoon meat mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Spread potatoes evenly over meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Make into 1-inch balls.
Put 3 at a time in a large bag of Shake 'n Bake (barbecue).
Bake at 450° for 5 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: festive sweet potatoes
directions: Pare cucumbers and cut lengthwise in very thick slices.
Wipe them dry with a cloth.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and dredge with flour.
Fry in pan greased with about 1 tablespoon each of lard and butter.
Brown both sides and serve warm.

title: chicken breast and stuffing casserole
directions: Put chicken in bottom of a casserole.
Cover chicken with celery, onion, parsley, water chestnuts, salt and pepper.
Mix soups together with Miracle Whip and spread on top of casserole. Top with stuffing and pour melted butter over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and soda.
Boil shortening, butter or oleo, water and cocoa and pour over dry ingredients above. After mixing the mixture, add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.

title: spring coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Spread 3/4 c. of the coconut evenly in shallow pan. Toast 7

to 12 minutes or until lightly browned, stirring frequently. Cool. Pour milk into large bowl. Add pudding mixes. Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes. Let stand 1 minute or until thickened. Gently stir in 1 c. of the whipped topping and remaining 1 c. untoasted coconut. Spread mixture in crust. Stir 1/2 c. of the toasted coconut into remaining whipped topping. Spread over pudding layer. Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 c. toasted coconut. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Store leftover pie, covered, in refrigerator.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Beat whole eggs, gradually adding sugar.
Add milk, salt, vanilla, coconut and nutmeg.
Pour into pastry shell; bake in moderate oven for 30 minutes, or until custard is firm.

title: party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and water.
Add sugar and juices.
Just before serving, add sherbet and ginger ale.

title: baked chicken maryland
directions: Butter a large casserole dish.
Wash chicken.
Mix the flour, salt and pepper; roll chicken in it.
Dip each piece in the egg, beaten slightly with the 2 tablespoons water.
Roll each piece in the bread crumbs; place in dish.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for about 45 minutes, or until tender.
Baste occasionally with margarine, lemon and 2 tablespoons water.
Serve alone or with gravy.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chili-mac supreme
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Boil macaroni until tender. Add chopped onion to ground beef just before it is done browning. In a large kettle over low heat, combine tomato juice, chili powder and salt.
Allow to start simmering.
Once it is simmering, add ground beef with onion and kidney beans.
Cook over very low heat for 1 hour.
Top with shredded cheese and serve.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: Brown onions in Crisco or oil.
Add paprika, chicken, salt and pepper and water to about cover chicken.
Cook until tender.

title: tallulah caboose fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs. Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes. Add vanilla. Combine dry ingredients (flour, soda, salt and cinnamon); add to mixture. Fold in chopped pecans and apples. Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake is done (check with a toothpick that pulls out clean from the cake).

title: dill dip
directions: Mix and chill overnight before serving.

title: winter fruit compote
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer the fruits in a casserole dish. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over fruit.
Cover and bake 1 hour until fruits are tender.
Allow to stand covered 45 minutes before serving.
Great side dish for holiday dinners!

title: vegetable 7 chicken pot pie
directions: In large skillet, melt butter.
Add celery and stir until crisp-tender.
Stir in soup, milk, onion powder and pepper; mix well.
Stir in vegetables and chicken; heat through.
Spoon into a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Arrange biscuits over hot filling.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind all vegetables in a grinder.
Add salt.
Let set 8 hours.
Wash and drain to remove salt.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup, soup mix, sour cream and chicken.
Place into a greased casserole.
Mix stuffing with water and butter according to package directions.
Spread over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.
May be frozen ahead.

title: banana cream walnut torte
directions: Sift sugar and baking powder together.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat in sugar mixture.
Fold in crackers, walnuts and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Spread onto a buttered 9-inch pie dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
(Torte will not brown.)
Cool in dish.

title: chili cheddar cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder, sugar and salt together. Add milk, eggs and shortening.
Mix together.
Add onion and let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in cheese, corn, green chili peppers and red peppers.
Spoon about 1/3 cup batter into greased and floured 2 1/2-inch muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 15 muffins.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in Pyrex bowl.
Mix other ingredients and pour (don't stir) into margarine.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Then pour over apples and cook in a hot water bath for 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon and set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in oats, chips and nuts.
Drop by measuring tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt together.
Pour into boiling water and cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla; stir until blended.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: pumpkin butter
directions: Bake in oven at 300° for 4 to 8 hours; stir frequently.
Makes 18 1/2 pints.

title: oriental salad
directions: Drain all juices off vegetables.
Marinate vegetables with remaining ingredients.

title: cookie fruit cobbler
directions: Pour fruit pie filling in a well greased 9 by 9-inch casserole dish.
Spoon cookie dough by scant teaspoons over fruit filling. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar evenly.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar and water until forms a soft ball.
Add Creme, vanilla and nuts.
Pour in buttered dish to cool, then cut in squares.

title: fruit salad pudding(excellent)
directions: Cook macaroni and set aside.
Mix together egg, sugar and flour.
Add to juice and cook until thick.
Pour over macaroni and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, add Cool Whip and drained fruit to macaroni.
Ready to serve.
Makes large salad.

title: lemon-lime jello salad
directions: Prepare lime and lemon jello as directed on box.
Melt cream cheese in warm jello mixture and let gel a little.
Add crushed pineapple and whipped Dream Whip to other ingredients and fold all together.
Let jell in refrigerator.

title: bundt cake
directions: Bake cake as box directions.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
When cake is done, turn out of pan on serving plate.
When cool, frost cake with frosting.

title: meal-in-one casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Add tomato soup and water.
Add package of noodles and cover.
Cook until noodles are tender.
Add corn, sugar, hot sauce and ketchup to noodle mixture. Pour half into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Grate half of cheese on top, then pour rest of mixture and grate remaining cheese on top.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes.
Serve with bread or crackers for complete meal.

title: pu pu's
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a saucepan and boil until thick.
Add sausages and keep mixture warm until sausages are heated thoroughly.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix and cook cake by the recipe on the box.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and make holes all over the top.
Mix cream coconut and condensed milk; pour over cake that has the holes in it.
Put a large container of Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Keep refrigerated.
It also freezes well.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Cut chicken in cubes.
Saute in small amount of oil.
Add sauce.
Let simmer while rice cooks in water.
Serve rice topped with chicken mix.

title: pineapple appetizers
directions: Wrap water chestnut and pineapple chunk in bacon and secure with a toothpick.
Dip in lemon juice; set aside in dish in 1 layer.
When dish is filled, sprinkle with teriyaki marinade.
Let stand a few hours or overnight.

title: broiled mustard-dill salmon
directions: Preheat broiler.

Set oven rack 4 to 5 inches from element. Rinse fish; pat dry and lay skin side down on a baking sheet. With a zester or grater, remove zest (yellow part of peel only) from lemon; squeeze 1 tablespoon juice from lemon.
Mix lemon zest, lemon juice, mustard and dill.
Brush mixture over salmon. Broil salmon until opaque in center (about 5 to 6 minutes for 1/2-inch thick fillet), 10 to 12 minutes for 1-inch fillet. Serves 2 to 4.
Great for grill, too!

title: flowerpot cake
directions: Crush cookies in a plastic bag with a rolling pin or food processor; set aside.
Cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
In another bowl, cream milk, pudding and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Line a clean flowerpot with plastic wrap.
Fill pot with alternating layers of cookie crumbs and pudding mixture.
Garnish with gummy worms or silk flowers.
Serves 12.

title: drop cookies
directions: Mix well and using a teaspoon, drop spoonfuls of batter on an ungreased cookie sheet, 2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bambini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese in small bowl.
Halve each biscuit horizontally, forming 20 thin biscuits.
Gently shape each piece of dough into an oval (2 1/2 x 4-inch).
Place a pepperoni on one end with a tablespoon of cheese mixture on top.
Moisten edges; fold dough over to enclose filling, pinching edges to seal.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cook until golden brown (10 to 12 minutes). Serve warm.

title: sante fe soup
directions: In a dutch oven, cook meat and onion till meat is brown and onion is tender, drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients, blending well.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 2 hours.
Top individual serving with grated cheese and sour cream.

title: apple and nut cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl; add apples, eggs, oil, vanilla and nuts.
Blend
together until moistened.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x
9-inch
pan
and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw and drain spinach, pressing out water well. Mix all ingredients and shape into 3/4-inch balls. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: dutch family cake
directions: Melt chocolate; blend with melted shortening.
Cool; stir in sugar, eggs, applesauce, vanilla and pecans.
Sift baking powder, baking soda and salt with flour.
Stir in chocolate mixture and bake in greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: delicious banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of a loaf pan.
Mix sugar and margarine in a 2 or 3 quart bowl.
Stir in eggs until blended.
Add bananas and water.
Beat 30 seconds.
Stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened.
Pour into pan.
Bake until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean (8-inch loaf 1 1/4 hours, 9-inch loaf 55 to 60 minutes); cool 5 minutes. Loosen sides of loaf from pan; remove from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Add first 4 ingredients and boil 1 minute.
Then add remaining ingredients.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Crust:
Mix pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fire house special
directions: Combine ingredients in proportions in keeping with number to be served.
(One box and 1 can each for family of four; increase for more servings.)
Bake in casserole dish, or heat together on stove until heated through.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Break half the buns (1 1/2) in bottom of large flat pan; add chopped peaches.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, liquid and oleo. Boil until oleo is melted and slightly thick.
Pour over peaches. Break remaining buns over top.
Push down into juice.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until slightly browned.
A good way to use stale buns or leftover buns.

title: no-fail pie crust
directions: Mix thoroughly flour, salt, sugar and shortening.
Add water, vinegar and egg.
Roll out on floured waxed paper and cut to the desired size.
The recipe makes four 9-inch pie crusts.
The extra crusts may be frozen for later use by separating crusts with sheets of waxed paper.
With the wax paper below and above a crust, fold the crust in half twice.
Place in a plastic bag, squeeze out the excess air, seal and freeze.
Thaw before unfolding.
Can be frozen in a lump and thawed and rolled out later.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Line bottom of 3 (9-inch) cake pans with waxed paper. Melt chocolate squares with water. Can be on stove top or in microwave. Mix flour with baking soda and salt; set aside. Beat oleo and sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well. Stir in melted chocolate and vanilla. Add flour mixture alternating with buttermilk, beating well. Beat egg whites until they form stiff peaks. Gently stir into the batter. Pour into pans. Bake for 30 minutes. Remove from oven. Run spatula between cake and sides of pan while hot. Let cool for 15 minutes still in pans. Remove and peel off paper.

title: jello delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and cool.
Cream the cheese with salad dressing, add the pineapple and nuts through the cream mixture and the whipping cream.
Add the bananas last.
Chill and serve.
Will keep for a couple days in refrigerator.

title: crustless apple pie
directions: Combine egg, sugar, apples and nuts.
Sift remaining ingredients together; add to first mixture.
Pour into greased pie plate.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rich brownies(with a wonderful cream frosting)
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Add cooled melted chocolate and blend.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in walnuts.
Bake in greased 8-inch square pan in moderate oven at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost with Creamy Chocolate Frosting.

title: old fashioned beef stew
directions: In large heavy pan, brown meat in shortening.
Pour off fat. Add soups, water and seasoning.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; cook 1 hour more or until tender.
Stir now and then.
Uncover and cook until desired consistency.
Makes 6 servings.

title: o' henry bars
directions: Mix oatmeal, sugars and oleo.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes; cool.
Melt chocolate chips. Add peanut butter.
Spread on crust.
Chill; cut into squares.

title: sausage balls
directions: Soften cheese and sausage to room temperature.
Combine with other ingredients.
Form in balls 1-inch in diameter, pop in 300° oven for 10 minutes.
These freeze well uncooked.
Cook without defrosting in 300° oven for 10 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and shape into a loaf.
Top with barbecue sauce.

title: refrigerator lemon pickles
directions: Put zucchini or cucumbers in a bowl with green pepper and onion.
Mix with salt and celery seed.
Let stand at room temperature 1 hour.

title: carrot marshmallow salad
directions: Peel carrots and shred into mixing bowl.
Add marshmallows, pineapple, raisins and coconut.
Toss lightly.
Combine mayonnaise and whipped cream.
Add to carrot mixture.
Freezes nicely.
Eat frozen or fresh.

title: nutty peach cobbler
directions: Put melted margarine evenly in bottom of long glass baking dish. Sprinkle brown sugar over margarine. Add walnuts over brown sugar. Add the peaches over the brown sugar and nuts. Mix batter of flour, sugar and milk; pour evenly over peaches. Bake approximately 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Top with Ritz crackers and melted butter.

title: buttery corn bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Combine the eggs and milk.
Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with egg mixture.
Pour into a greased 13 X 9 X 2 inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 22-27 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cut into squares; serve warm.
Yield: 12-15 servings.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Melt cream cheese and margarine together.
Mix in flour with fork.
Pat crust to fit pan.
Bake at 450° or as directed for pie.

title: quick pickled peaches
directions: Use liquid from 1 can of the peaches.
Add sugar, vinegar and pickling spices.
Mix together and bring to a boil.
Add drained peaches.
Remove from heat and allow to cool.
Store in refrigerator in tightly covered container.

title: apple pie (mom's)
directions: Mix with cold water.
Put this into a pie shell (top and bottom).
Bake at 350° until done.

title: italian sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until mixture clings together.
Roll into small balls about an inch in diameter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 350 degrees 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 8 doz. sausage balls.

title: tomato chicken curry
directions: Saute onions and garlic in olive oil.
Add spices.
Remove garlic.
Fry chicken in spice mixture for about 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes; simmer for another 30 minutes.
Add yogurt just before serving.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all together the hash brown potatoes, cream of chicken soup and Cheddar cheese.
Pour in buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Put crushed cornflakes over top.
Melt margarine and drizzle over cornflakes.
Bake 1 hour at 350° to 375°.

title: cheesecake crunch bars
directions: Combine butterscotch morsels and margarine.
Heat until melted and smooth.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs and nuts with a fork until mixture forms small crumbs.
Reserve 2 cups crumb mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture into an ungreased oblong cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: fresh broccoli mandarin salad(10 to 12 servings)
directions: Toss all ingredients together and chill.

title: ziti bake
directions: About 1 hour before serving:
In 8-quart Dutch oven prepare ziti as label directs; drain and set aside.

title: colossal cookie
directions: Beat sugar, margarine and syrup.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Slowly mix in dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips. Refrigerate for 1-1/2 hours or freeze 3/4 hour.
Place in 12 inch round foil pan.
Press to within 1-1/2 in. of edge.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes.

title: walnut balls
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar slowly and cream.
Add flour in 2 parts, chopped nuts, vanilla and salt.
Chill overnight.
Roll into small balls to size and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: easy chili
directions: Combine all ingredients; cook until meat is done.
Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Fritos.
Chill.
Just prior to serving, add Fritos.

title: spaghetti, eggplant and pepper
directions: Dice eggplant; salt and leave to stand an hour or more, covered with a weighted plate.
Fry garlic and parsley in oil. Add eggplant with a pinch of ground chili powder (or chili pepper).
Cut peppers in strips and cook with the vegetables for 15 minutes over moderate heat, then over low heat until tender. Stir in tomato sauce.
Cook pasta; drain well and mix with sauce.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda, cloves, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt together in a large bowl.
Set aside.
Then in a large bowl, mix together oil, sugars, pumpkin and eggs.
Then add flour mixture, mixing well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° in metal pans or 325° in glass pans for 1 hour, covering with foil for the last 20 minutes so it won't get too brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes.
After it comes to a boil, drain real well.
Make sauce in large pan.
Mix sauce with broccoli, lightly, and put in a buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with finely rolled Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: dawn's fudge
directions: Lightly grease 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Combine dry ingredients in heavy 4-quart saucepan.
Stir in milk; bring to full (bubbly) boil over medium heat without stirring to 234° (soft ball stage). Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cool at room temperature to 110°.
(Pan should be barely warm to touch.) Beat with wooden spoon until fudge thickens and loses its gloss. Quickly spread in pan.
Cool, then cut.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar, Bisquick and part of milk to make a stiff dough mixture.
Put a thin layer of dough mixture on bottom of well-greased pan.
Add rest of milk to dough mixture and stir well.
Place fruit on top of dough mixture already in pan.
Pour rest of dough mixture over fruit.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: lemon pies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; mix well.
Save egg whites for topping.
Pour mixed ingredients into pie crusts.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli, celery and onion in 2 cups water until done. Heat butter in 3-quart saucepan.
Add flour; heat until bubbly. Add 2 1/2 cups water; boil one minute.
Stir in (blended) veggies. Add bouillon, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Heat to boiling and add whipping cream.
Do not boil cream.

title: spanish whipped cream cake
directions: Add cinnamon, oil and sugar to cake mix. Also add what mix calls for. Stir and bake as directed on box. Can make 2 or 3 layers. Pam spray 9-inch round or square cake pans.

title: coconut sour cream dream cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions, making two 8-inch layers.
Split both layers horizontally after they have cooled. Blend together the sugar, sour cream and fresh frozen coconut. Chill.

title: general cleaning solution
directions: (It suds less if you put the water in the gallon first and then add other ingredients.)
Mix ingredients together in a gallon jug.
Transfer to a spray bottle.
Label bottle.
Excellent for many household chores!

title: speedy chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix by directions on box.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together sugar and cocoa. Sprinkle over top of cake. Pour boiling water over the cake. Bake according to package directions until firm on top.
Serve hot.
Spoon cake and sauce into a bowl and top with whipped topping, cherries or orange slices.

title: orange pop jello
directions: Boil 1 cup pop.
Mix with jello; stir until dissolved.
Add the rest of the pop.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
With mixer, fold in Cool Whip.
Add mandarin oranges.
Pour into serving dish or mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Add all dry ingredients with shortening and mix good and fine.
Add milk and mix until forms dough.
Do not over mix as dough will get tough.
Roll out about 1/8 to 1/4 inch thick.
Cut squares big enough to cover whole apple.
Sprinkle a little sugar and cinnamon in center of apple and wrap in dough.
Place in baking pan about 1 to 2 inches apart.
Pour syrup over apples, and then bake at 375° for about 35 minutes or until knife inserts easily.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Scald milk; add butter and cool, slightly.
Add eggs and sugar.
When warm, add yeast to milk and mix with salt and flour.
Let rise good.
Roll out and cut round; brush with butter.
Double over and place in buttered pan. Let raise and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: most excellent nacho dish
directions: In order listed, layer all ingredients in an oblong cake pan. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve as a dip with taco chips.

title: molasses layer cake
directions: Put molasses on stove to warm, then stir in soda and take off stove.
The molasses will turn yellow.
Beat eggs lightly. Now in molasses, stir in all ingredients (except apple) and enough flour to make dough like biscuit dough.
Grease cake pan. Roll out or pat in a thin layer.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Between layers place apples.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Melt margarine on low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir up until melted.
Cook over low heat for 3 more minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies and stir well. Press evenly into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: potatoes gourmet
directions: Boil the potatoes in skins.
Cool, peel and shred on coarse grater.
Combine cheese and 4 tablespoons butter in saucepan. Heat and stir until cheese is almost melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Fold in potatoes. Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Cover and bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Peel and mash potatoes. Blend in egg, 2 tablespoons margarine and pineapple juice or cream. Add salt and nutmeg. Divide into 6 portions.
Mold each portion around 1 marshmallow to form a ball. Add remaining 2 tablespoons melted margarine to crushed corn flakes. Roll sweet potato balls in margarine and corn flake mixture.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: voodoo stew(geri morris' recipe)
directions: Heat oil.
Add onion, celery and carrots.
Saute over moderate heat, stirring, until onion is transparent.
Add broth.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Add zucchini, salt, pepper, herbs and vinegar.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and olives.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until vegetables are done.
Dissolve cornstarch in a small amount of the cooking liquid.
Stir into stew.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring until thickened.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix the night before you ice the cake.
Keep in refrigerator. Bake 2 layer yellow cake mix; cool and split in layers.
Ice cake and refrigerate.

title: lazy day stew
directions: Arrange meat in roaster or casserole in single layer (don't brown meat first).
Place vegetables on top of meat.
Mix tomato sauce with water and sugar.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Add salt and pepper.
Scatter tapioca on top.
Seal roaster in heavy foil.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.
Do not open oven during recommended cooking time.
When foil is removed, meat will be brown with gravy.

title: spaghetti chicken casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and set aside.
Cook pepper and onion in chicken broth until tender.
Add cheese, soups and seasonings; stir.
Add chicken and spaghetti.
Mix well and pour into large baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and gradually add milk, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Combine flour and water and add to mixture.
Transfer to unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 375° for 25 minutes.
Then check and add time, if necessary.

title: maple syrup muffins
directions: Mix together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in the center.
In a separate bowl, mix egg, milk, syrup and butter.
Pour liquid mixture into dry mixture; combine thoroughly. Spoon mixture into greased muffin pan for 12 muffins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: lee's favorite cole slaw
directions: Wash, cut and shred cabbage in food processor (or by hand). Peel carrot, cut off ends and shred with cabbage.
Add pickles, sugar and mayo.
Mix well. Serve cold with seafood, barbecue or on hot dogs.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All, then combine cream of chicken soup and mayo. Put in baking dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Add crackers (crushed), nuts and vanilla; stir to mix.
Pour in large, buttered 9 x 13-inch dish and cook 25 minutes at 325°.
Let cool.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken in enough water to cover until done, approximately 15 to 20 minutes and save the broth.
Remove chicken, boil pasta in the same broth until half done.
Mix soup, Cheez Whiz and chilies into boiling noodles and stir until smooth. Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add shredded chicken and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°, uncovered.
Serve bubbling hot.

title: pineapple bran muffins
directions: In bowl, pour milk over bran cereal buds.
In another bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add pineapple, oil and egg to cereal; mix well.
Add to flour mixture; stir until moistened.
Spoon into 12 paper-lined muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: blueberry banana muffins(yields 1 dozen muffins)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix in bananas and milk.
In another mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add margarine mixture to dry ingredients; mix only until moist.
Stir in whole blueberries.
If adding frozen ones, add them to your mixture while still frozen.
Spoon batter into greased muffin cups, filling cup to top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until muffins are golden brown.
Let cool for 5 minutes, then transfer to cooling rack.

title: apple butter(sugar-free)
directions: Peel and core apples; cut in chunks.
Simmer in apple juice with spices for 15 minutes.
Cool and puree.
Simmer again until desired consistency.
Stir in sweetener.

title: cherry loaf
directions: Drain red cherries (save liquid, add water if needed to equal 1/3 cup).
Cut up cherries.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In separate bowl beat eggs, add milk, oil, applesauce and cherry liquid.
Stir wet ingredients into dry ingredients.
Fold in red and green cherries, pecans and orange peel.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tests done.

title: gammon and spinach
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces and fry in large skillet.
Drain off all but approximately 2 tablespoons of grease.
In a large jar mix sugar, vinegar, water and flour.
Shake vigorously until creamy.
Add to pan; add spinach.
Slice eggs and add to pan. Cook approximately 5 minutes.
Serve over mashed potatoes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix in a large bowl; cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine the flour and baking powder.
Add to butter mixture alternately with milk.
Add flavoring and mix well. Place dough on a floured board and knead.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thick and cut or roll out like biscuits.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: rigatoni with sausage
directions: Cut sausage in 1-inch pieces.
Place in hot skillet with olive oil.
Brown slightly, about 10 minutes.
Add onion, mushrooms (well cleaned and sliced), garlic, salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add tomato puree and bay leaf, cover and cook slowly for 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf.
Cook rigatoni about 20 minutes in 5 quarts rapidly boiling water (salted).
Drain and place in baking dish.
Add sausage and sauce; mix.
Sprinkle with grated macaroni cheese and bake in moderate oven about 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and mix other ingredients except cracker crumbs together.
Crumble cracker crumbs on top.
Dot with butter and bake until brown, about 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chile relleno casserole
directions: Oil a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drain chiles and place half of them in bottom of pan (open chiles if necessary to cover bottom). Sprinkle half the cheese.
Beat eggs and thinned sour cream with flour and pour over chiles.
Poke with fork to be sure batter seeps through.
Sprinkle top with parsley and garlic powder. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, until the top is golden.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare 1 box stuffing mix as directed; set aside.
Boil chicken in water until done.
Drain.
Let chicken set in cold water until cool enough to strip from bones.
After cooling, place chicken in oblong cake pan, ungreased.
Pour mixture of soups over meat strips.
Stir together.
Spoon and spread dressing over mixture, pushing 2/3 of stuffing down into mixture.
Stuffing makes a light crunchy top.
Sprinkle with pepper and bake in preheated oven (350°) for 1 hour.

title: spicy turkey roast
directions: Remove mesh from turkey.
Lay turkey out as flat as possible on cutting board, placing skin side down.
Combine the garlic, rosemary, pepper and salt in the work bowl of a food processor with the steel blade in place or in blender.
Add oil, processing until coarsely chopped.

title: granny tiner's sour orange pie
directions: Separate the yolks and whites.
Mix yolks and sugar.
Beat whites until stiff.
Combine yolks with whites, then add juice. Pour as much as possible into the pie shell.
Bake for about 5 minutes at 350° and remove from oven.
Use a fork to pull skim open in center and then pour your remaining mix into the hole. Continue baking until brown.
(I forgot how long this takes?) This is my favorite!

title: bacon horseradish dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill one hour.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Bake sausage in shallow pan for 25 minutes at 400°.
Turn sausage once.
Place layers of noodles in casserole.
Dribble 4 tablespoons sausage drippings over top.
Add applesauce, lemon juice and spices, then another layer of noodles.
Place sausage on top and sprinkle grated cheese over all.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook sliced zucchini and chopped onion in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes; then drain.
Combine soup and sour cream. Stir in shredded carrot.
Fold in drained zucchini and onion. Combine stuffing and margarine. Spread half of mixture in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top, then cover with remaining stuffing.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: butterscotch chews
directions: Melt morsels.
Add noodles and cashews.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: chocolate-mocha frozen dessert
directions: Beat together the cream cheese, milk, chocolate syrup and dissolved instant coffee.
Pour mixture over prepared crust and top with chopped pecans.
Freeze overnight.

title: cool cucumber salad
directions: Add cucumber and onion to sour cream, milk, salt and pepper. Allow to refrigerate overnight for better flavor.

title: breakaway vegetable bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.

Dip each piece in margarine and layer 1/3 of the biscuits in a lightly greased 10-inch Bundt pan. Sprinkle with half the bacon, cheese, onion and green pepper. Repeat layers until all ingredients are used, ending with biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: sweet potato casserole(with topping)
directions: Combine and put in 9 x 13 pan. Add topping.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in baking dish.
Mix sugar with 1/2 of pineapple juice or syrup.
Pour over pork chops.
Bake 25 minutes, until sauce is bubbling.
Place pineapple slice on each pork chop and a cherry in the center of each pineapple.
Spoon sauce over pork chops some more.
Return to oven for about 5 minutes.

title: sausage and sauerkraut dinner
directions: Brown sausage in butter in a 1 1/2-quart Dutch oven or large casserole.
Arrange onion, sauerkraut, apples and potatoes around sausage.
Top with apple juice, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover tightly and simmer over low heat, stirring once, for 30 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Toss together and put into flat casserole dish.
Top with 1/4 pound lightly cooked bacon strips.
Bacon cooked 3/4 done.
Also top with 1/2 cup sliced stuffed olives (optional).
Bake at 325° for about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; place in greased 9 x 12-inch dish.
Top with chicken.
Mix soup, lemon juice, mayonnaise and curry powder. Pour on chicken.
Add cheese.
Top with cracker crumbs mixed with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: aunt flossie's pepper relish
directions: Roast pimientos in slow oven.
Cool and peel.
Coarsely grind pimientos, onions and hot peppers.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly, stirring constantly, cooking for about 20 minutes. After mixture is thoroughly hot, pour in jars and seal.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in separate saucepans until done (wild rice 30 to 45 minutes).
Fry bacon and remove from pan to dry; save grease. Cool bacon and break in small pieces.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Thaw strawberries.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Stir in food coloring.
Put lemon juice and water in a custard cup and sprinkle gelatin over top.
Let sit about 5 minutes to soften. Place custard cup in a small saucepan, surround with a small amount of water and then heat over low heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Blend gelatin into strawberries.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken, then whip the chilled evaporated milk until it is stiff and will hold a peak.
Fold in gelatin mixture lightly but thoroughly.
If necessary, chill until mixture mounds when dropped from spoon.
Pile lightly into 4 cups.
Chill until set.

title: paella with peas and carrots
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil in a Dutch oven; remove chicken.
Add onion and garlic to pan; cook over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until tender.
Add chicken, tomatoes and salt.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: oven doughnuts
directions: Mix oil, milk and sugar. Add egg, beat well. Add remaining ingredients. Mix until smooth. Pour into greased muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from tins and roll in melted butter and then in mixture of 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates, let stand for 10 minutes.
Add sugar to beaten egg; sift together all dry ingredients, stir in walnuts.
Add date mixture alternately with the sifted dry ingredients to the sugar/egg mixture.
Stir in shortening and vanilla.
Pour into well greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: salmon salad
directions: In bowl, combine red salmon, minced clams, diced celery, hard-cooked eggs, water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Combine mayonnaise lemon juice, salt and pepper. Add to salmon mixture and toss lightly.
Cover, chill and serve. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken provencale
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In bowl toss potatoes, onions, tomatoes and olives with oil until well blended.
Remove skin from chicken, except wings.
Place chicken, vegetable mixture and bay leaves in large roasting pan.
Sprinkle with salt, thyme and oregano.
Bake until juices run clear when chicken is pierced with fork and vegetables are tender, about 45 minutes.
Remove bay leaves before serving.
Makes 8 servings, 201 calories per serving.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix together and heat slowly.
Serve hot.
Use crackers for dip.
Serves about 12 as an hors d'oeuvre.

title: white mountain fudge
directions: In saucepan, combine milk, syrup and salt.
Cook until forms a soft ball in water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Beat well.
Add nuts and/or fruits. Pour into well buttered pan.
Cut into squares.

title: fish, chicken or veal parmesan
directions: Bread meat or fish as desired.
Either bake in oven or deep fry until tender.
Top with favorite marinara sauce, followed by Parmesan cheese, Provolone cheese and a little more sauce.
Return to oven until the cheese melts.
Serve with a side order of angel hair pasta, topped with marinara sauce.

title: corn cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put on hot griddle, like pancakes. Great with your favorite syrup!

title: everyday dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add the shortening, salt and sugar; allow to cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; add to mixture. Add the flour to the liquid gradually, mixing well after each addition until a soft dough is formed.
Cover the bowl tightly, set in warm place, and allow to rise until double in bulk.
Turn onto a floured board; knead until the dough can be easily handled and mold into rolls.
Place in a well-greased pan; let rise again until double in bulk.
Bake in a hot oven (375°) for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: orange jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and add sherbet.
Add oranges and bananas.
Pour into mold and let set.

title: lime sling
directions: Pour hot tea over lemon and lime slices.
Let stand 30 minutes; strain.

title: fried lumpia
directions: Brown ground beef in a large pan.
Drain grease and return beef to the pan.
Add vegetables and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add about 1 tablespoon soy sauce (more if desired).
Let mixture cool.
Separate the egg.
Add the egg yolk to meat mixture and reserve the egg white for sealing the lumpia wrappers. Separate lumpia wrappers carefully and prevent them from drying out.
Spoon about 1 1/2 tablespoons of the beef mixture 1/4 down one end and pull that 1/4 end over mixture.
Roll up tightly and seal the wrapper with egg whites.
Deep-fry in oil until golden brown or pan-fry in some oil (I prefer deep frying).
Drain on paper towels and serve hot with some ketchup, sweet and sour sauce or barbecue sauce.
Leftovers can be reheated in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: papas en escabeche
directions: Use 2-quart covered bowl, preferably with sealed lid.
Boil and cool carrots, eggs (hard) and potatoes.
Peel potatoes.
Make three alternating layers with the following ingredients:
2 potatoes, 2 eggs, 1/3 of carrots, 1/3 of onion, 1 sliced jalapeno, salt, pepper and paprika.
After third layer, add salad oil and 1/2 cup of juice from can of peppers and vinegar.
Seal tightly with cover and refrigerate overnight, occasionally turning upside-down, then over again.
Serve cold the next day.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake cookies are directed. Cool. Frost with cream cheese and top with desired fruit.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Spread pineapple on bottom of lightly greased baking dish. Cover with blueberries.
Add 1/2 cup sugar sprinkled over berries. Sprinkle dry cake mix over sugar.
Melt butter and pour evenly over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: willy's buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter with butter then add powdered sugar mix with hands and shape balls and roll in chocolate.
Lay on wax paper to harden.

title: quick cheesy beef dinner
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper.
Set aside.
Cook macaroni dinner as directed on box.
Then mix the beef mixture with macaroni. Ready to serve.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Layer in large casserole (13 x 9 x 2) the chicken, onion, 1/2 cheese and corn chips. Mix together soups and chicken stock. Pour over chicken, then pour over salsa. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake at 325° for about an hour.

title: fourth of july cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake in 13x9x2 inch pan, according to package directions.
Cool cake in pan on wire rack.
Turn cake out onto serving platter.
Frost cake with whipped topping.
Decorate top of cake as flag:
Arrange blueberries in upper left-hand corner of cake.

Make 13 stripes across cake, starting with stripe of strawberries across top, then leaving stripe of white topping showing through, and repeating the alternate stripes until you have 13 (7 red and 6 white).
Cut and serve.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble. Cook carrot and onion in bacon drippings.
Remove from pan. Scramble eggs and remove from pan.
Fry ham or chicken.
Remove from pan. Place rice in pan. Add soy sauce, salt and green pepper. Stir until heated.
Add all ingredients. Serve hot with additional soy sauce, if desired.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Roll chicken breasts in Contadina seasoned bread crumbs. Brown in Pam or butter.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add a slice of Muenster cheese to each piece of chicken.
Pour sliced mushrooms over the chicken.
Pour a small amount of chicken broth (about 1/4 way up) on the chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes.
In large skillet, saute chicken and garlic in oil until chicken is partially cooked.
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Stir in 2 cups water, reserved pineapple syrup, rice, vinegar, brown sugar, soy sauce, salt, ginger and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 12 minutes or until rice is almost tender.
Cut green and red peppers into 1-inch pieces; add pineapple chunks.
Combine 3 tablespoons cold water and cornstarch; quickly stir into stew mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer an additional 10 to 15 minutes or until rice and green pepper are tender.

title: strawberry delight punch
directions: In blender container, combine strawberries, lemonade concentrate, sugar and Nestea.
Process at high speed until smooth.
Pour into serving pitcher.
Stir in cold water.
Makes 12 (4 ounce) servings.

title: carrot ring
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding the beaten egg whites last. Pour into a buttered mold.
Set in water; cook for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Unmold and fill center with mushroom sauce.

title: chocolate marshmallow sundae cake
directions: Mix syrup and water together.
Pour into pans.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Carefully pour cake batter onto syrup mixture. Bake at 375° until done.
May be served warm with ice cream topping using chocolate syrup in bottom of pan as topping.

title: honey nut bars
directions: Mix all ingredients and pat dough over ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning; let stand a few hours.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef; add taco seasoning.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cool. Mix in remaining ingredients except tomatoes.
Add tomatoes just before serving.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix softened butter, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mix flour and baking powder; add to butter mixture.
Mix well.
Grease a cookie sheet and dust lightly with flour.
Drop dough mixture by teaspoons on the cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: rick's baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except hamburger.
Brown the hamburger and add to beans.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.
(B&M beans are best as they don't get mushy.)

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and butter.
Press in bottom of pan.
Mix well the confectioners sugar, cream cheese and 3 eggs.
Pour over cake mix and bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Gradually add sugar until fluffy. Gradually mix in flour.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Press mixture into two 9-inch glass pie pans.
Score into wedges and pierce with fork.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Cut wedges.
Cool on rack.
Makes 16 wedges.

title: chili for forty
directions: Brown meat in heavy big pot.
When meat loses the pink color, add flour and seasonings.
Mix well, then add tomato juice.
Let simmer as long as possible.
Cool.
Remove fat from top, then reheat to serve.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and water.
Cook until thick, approximately 45 minutes.
Add peanuts and stir continuously until syrup turns light brown and peanuts are done (1 hour).
Remove from heat and add salt, soda and butter.
Stir until mixed well.
Pour into a buttered cookie sheet.
Spread as thin as possible.

title: heavenly hamburger
directions: Brown meat, garlic, salt, pepper and sugar in oleo; drain. Add tomato sauce; simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed; drain.
Soften cream cheese; add to sour cream and onions.
Combine meat mixture and noodles (or lasagna).
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan or casserole.
Spread sour cream mixture over meat and noodles.
Spread Cheddar cheese over this.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8 or more.

title: pecan supreme
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans into crumb mixture and press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Beat powdered sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese and pour over first layer.
Beat pudding and milk together and spread over second layer.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans. Refrigerate and serve.

title: southwest dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Serve with vegetables or tortilla chips.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring shortening and water to a boil. Add flour and salt quickly and stir constantly until mixture leaves the sides of the pan and forms a ball, about 1 minute. Remove from heat and cool slightly. Beat with mixer, adding eggs 1 at a time and beating until smooth after each addition. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes. Fill, either by cutting off top of each puff or with pastry bag, with vanilla pudding. Frost with chocolate icing.

title: jeff's salsa
directions: Dice onions, cilantro leaves only and chiles and mince garlic. Take cans of whole tomatoes and blend in blender slightly, remove and place in bowl.
Cut all jalapenos into slices and blend in blender to a paste.
Add all ingredients in bowl and stir.
Season and stir.

title: sweet nothings
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips together. Pour over cereal. Stir gently. Put powdered sugar in a brown paper bag or plastic food storage bag. Add the chocolate chex and shake.

title: instant cocoa
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Use 4 teaspoons to 1 cup of hot water.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread apples evenly in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place butter in a small glass mixing bowl.
Microwave for 45 seconds to 1 minute or until softened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until crumbly, then sprinkle over apples.
Microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until apples are tender.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: what to do with carrots or renee's remainder
directions: Cut carrots in disk shape.
Cut zucchini, yellow squash, broccoli and cauliflower as you like.
In a large saucepan, saute carrots in margarine.

title: pumpkin custard pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan. Separate eggs and beat egg whites and fold in after it is in pie pan.
Bake in a moderate oven until firm.
Makes 2 large pies.

title: stuffed flounder
directions: In skillet, cook onions in 1/4 cup butter until tender but not brown.
Stir drained mushrooms in skillet with flaked crab, cracker crumbs, parsley, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Spread mixture over flounder fillets.
Roll fillets and place seam side down in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
In saucepan, melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Blend in flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add enough milk to mushroom liquid to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add with wine to saucepan.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles. Pour over fillets.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Return to oven.
Bake 10 minutes longer or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Serves 8.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Cut margarine into flour; add remaining ingredients.
Press in 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375° and let cool.

title: corn relish
directions: Cut corn from cob.
Force cabbage through a grinder.
Separate celery stalks.
Remove leaves and chop.
Peel onions and cut in thin slices.
Wipe peppers and chop.
Put vegetables in preserving kettle and pour over 1 quart vinegar.
Mix sugar, flour, mustard, cayenne and turmeric.
Add to the other.

title: coon balls
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Roll into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: potato broccoli bake
directions: Place potatoes in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine margarine, salt, paprika and pepper.
Brush the margarine mixture onto the potatoes.
Bake uncovered at 425° for 45 minutes. Arrange broccoli over the potatoes and pour the pimento cheese sauce over the vegetables.
Cover and bake 10 minutes or until broccoli is tender.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Boil chicken; debone in bite-size pieces.
Mix together and bake 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Grate Cheddar cheese on top and put back in oven until cheese is melted in 350° oven.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into small balls.
Cook about 10 minutes at 350°.
Can be frozen.

title: cold cut bread
directions: Roll out dough (after it has reached room temperature) into a large oblong shape.
Cut meats into strips.
Cut Swiss cheese into strips.
Spread all meats evenly on dough, then spread Swiss and Mozzarella cheeses evenly over dough.
Roll dough up in jelly roll fashion.
Place seam down into a large greased cookie sheet. Brush bread with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with seeds, if so desired. Crimp ends.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
(If bread is very large, more baking time may be required.)

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.

title: swedish cole slaw
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar and oil to a boil and, while hot, pour over cabbage mixture.
Do not stir until cold.
Cover and put in refrigerator.
Will keep for days.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: raised donuts or coffee cake
directions: Mix milk, sugar, butter and salt until butter is melted.
Add yeast mixture and flour to make soft dough. Place dough on well floured board and knead until soft and elastic.
Roll dough about 1/2 inch thick; cut with round cutter, then cut small hole in center. (I use a glass and a 2 liter bottle cap.) Let rise until double in size, about 3 hours.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown. Drain on absorbent paper. Shake in bag with mixture of sugar and cinnamon or frost with your favorite frosting.

title: graham cracker eclair
directions: Layer crackers in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add layer of pudding mix; repeat 3 times.
Spread chocolate frosting on top. Refrigerate overnight and serve the next day.

title: hawaiian cheesecake
directions: Beat softened cream cheese with 1 1/2 cups milk until smooth. Add pudding mix and remaining milk, beating 1 minute. Fold dairy topping into the mixture. Melt butter in a 9 to 10-inch pie plate. Form a crust, working in as much coconut as possible. Press onto sides and bottom of pie plate. Bake at 300° for 20+ minutes. Cool. Fill and freeze. Serve frozen.

title: peach preserves
directions: You will also need 8 (1 cup) jelly jars, sterilized.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter and cook the onion a little before adding other ingredients.
Beat eggs first; add and combine all ingredients except cheese and place in baking dish; top with cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes until brown and puffy.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
