Combine flour, salt and sugar.
Add gradually to beaten eggs and continue beating until sugar is dissolved. Combine corn syrup, Dr.
Pepper and vanilla.
Add to beaten egg mixture along with melted margarine.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Combine chocolate pieces and pecans, sprinkle over top of the filling.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until well set, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Boil raspberry juice with sugar, cornstarch and spices.
When cool, add orange juice and grape juice.
Serve over cracked ice or freeze and serve as sherbet.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except egg whites.
In separate bowl beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in 3 greased and floured (8-inch) pans or 2 (9-inch) pans.

title: muddy buddies
directions: Pour cereal in large bowl.
In 1-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute. Stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Pour cereal mixture in large resealable plastic bag with powdered sugar.
Seal securely and shake until all pieces are well coated.
Spread on wax paper.

title: dry jello salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Add drained pineapples. Stir in dry jello.
Refrigerate.
This makes a delicious salad and will keep for several days.

title: cheese cake
directions: Blend all together in blender.
Pour into graham cracker shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes (until set).
Cool for 10 minutes on rack.

title: prissy pecans
directions: Cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour on waxed paper and push apart with spoon.

title: sweet spaghetti
directions: Cut bacon in chunks.
Put in a skillet and brown.
When bacon is almost brown, put in chopped onions.
Brown well.
Take bacon grease out (except 4 tablespoons).
Add tomato juice and sugar. Cook on medium for 15 minutes.
Then turn down to simmer.
Cook your noodles.
Add to sauce.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all beans and pimentos in colander.
Finely chop onions, green peppers and celery.
Add vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add drained vegetables.

title: crispy chicken bits
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry. Cut in 1-inch pieces.
In plastic bag, combine flour, parsley, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper. Add chicken pieces, a few at a time, to seasoned flour mix. Close bag and shake to coat pieces well.

title: basic nut bread
directions: Add and mix well by hand the first 7 ingredients.
Add last bananas and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 or so minutes.
Test doneness with broomstraw or cake tester.
For best moistness, only a few small crumbs should stick to tester wire.

title: pot roast meat loaf(serves 4 to 6)
directions: *Or mix 1 teaspoon salt, a few grains of pepper and 2 teaspoons dried parsley flakes and sprinkle on all.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season pork chops to taste.
Roll in flour, then brown on back side.
Cut up vegetables and set aside until you have browned the pork chops.
Saute vegetables in same skillet with the oil you cooked the chops in.
Place the chops in casserole pan.
After the vegetables are done, pour the tomato juice in with the vegetables. Take that and pour over the chops.
Simmer about 15 minutes in oven at 350°.
Serve with rice and tossed salad or mashed potatoes.

title: blt dip
directions: Mix together mayonnaise and sour cream.
Add cut up tomatoes. Fry bacon crisp; crumble and add to mixture.
Dip bagel chips.

title: old fashioned apple pie
directions: Line pie pan with pastry.
Mix sugar and cinnamon. Add apples and mix well.
Place apples in pan. Dot with butter.
Cover pie with crust, cutting slits for steam to escape.
Seal edges and flute.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 50 minutes or until crust is well browned and apples are cooked through. If edge seems to brown too quickly, cover with a strip of foil.

title: golden vegetable casserole
directions: Cut green peppers into thin strips and blanch in saucepan of boiling water for 5 to 7 minutes.
To destroy bitter flavor, place peppers and other vegetables in layers in a heavily buttered 2-quart casserole dish.

title: spinach cheese casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Combine with rest of ingredients except sliced cheese.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Break American cheese into pieces and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: spinach salad with walnuts
directions: Remove and discard woody stems of spinach. Wash spinach well. Spin to dry or dry with towels.
Tear spinach in pieces and place in salad bowl. Add drained water chestnuts. Remove and discard root and wilted ends of green onions, chop and sprinkle on salad.

title: chili con corny("a spicy corn chowder")
directions: Saute 1 large onion with the olive oil.
Add the remaining ingredients.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into 2 well-greased bread pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Place peppers in a boiler pan.
Cover with water and boil approximately 20 minutes.
Remove and drain.
Rinse in cold water until cool.
Mix beef, onion, ketchup, rice, salt and pepper well. Stuff peppers with meat mixture.
Place peppers in a baking dish. Bake in a 350° oven until meat is done.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Stir yeast and 1 tablespoon of sugar in warm water and let stand. Mix margarine, salt and milk in small sauce pan and heat until margarine is just melting. Stir in sugar

and egg. Add yeast mixture. Stir in most of flour. Use rest to knead in making a ball of dough. Place in a greased bowl and let rise until about double in size.(about one hour). Punch down and turn out on board and pinch into rolls. Place in greased pan. Let rise for about thirty minutes. Bake at 375 degrees until golden brown.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: In
bowl
combine
milk, sugar, eggs, vanilla, salt and nutmeg.
Beat
well
to
blend.
Sprinkle
coconut into pastry shell; pour
egg mixture over coconut.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes
or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool and serve garnished with whipped cream.

title: basic spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add egg, margarine and sugar. Mix well; stir in flour until mixture makes a smooth dough. Keep in large airtight container in refrigerator. When ready to bake, spoon dough into greased muffin pan. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes about 36 large rolls or 72 small rolls.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix well.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake 1 hour in greased and floured Bundt pan (may need to bake a little longer).
Remove from oven and cool 10 minutes.
Drizzle additional 1/2 stick melted butter.
Turn out of cake pan after cooling for 30 minutes.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: yum-yum pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients by hand and pat into greased cake pan. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°, then cool completely.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown hamburg and drain off grease.
Mix both jars of salsa, hamburg and 2 cups of cheese.
Put into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining 1 cup of cheese over the top.
Bake 30 minutes, uncovered, until bubbly, at 375°.
Serve with nacho chips and plenty of napkins!

title: seven layer salad
directions: Arrange lettuce in bottom of deep bowl.
In layers, add celery, green
pepper,
onions and peas.
Do not toss.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over layer of peas.
Sprinkle with sugar and cheese.
Cover;
refrigerate
for
at least 4 hours.
Sprinkle bacon over salad before serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: coconut pie crust
directions: Melt butter; stir in
other
ingredients.
Press into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool before filling.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick and cut out with doughnut cutter.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown on both sides.
Drain well on paper towels.

title: joan's spicy hot black-eyed peas
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon; crumble and set aside or substitute oil.
Stir next 11 ingredients into bacon drippings or oil in skillet.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour mixture into serving dish. Sprinkle bacon and parsley over top.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mile high raspberry pie
directions: Beat whites until fluffy.
Add berries, sugar and juice and beat at high speed for 15 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream and pour into baked pie shell or crumb crust.
Freeze several hours.
Cut and serve at once after removing from freezer.

title: turnip puff
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in greased casserole and bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: original green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 can onions.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes or until onions are golden.
Makes 6 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add flour and milk as for white sauce. Add sugar and cheese; let cheese melt.
Blend in sour cream.
Mix part of this mixture with drained beans.
Put in casserole dish; pour remaining sauce on top.
Cover with crushed corn flakes; dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Heat thoroughly.

title: citrus veal
directions: Pound medallions of veal into 4 x 5-inch pieces. Add tarragon to veal slices. Blanch carrots in water until crunchy. Drain. Place vegetables on veal slices. Wrap veal around vegetables and secure with toothpicks. Lightly roll veal in flour. Saute veal rolls in clarified butter for 2 minutes. Remove veal to pie tin and hold in warming oven. Add ginger and cook for 15 seconds. Deglaze with white wine; reduce by half. Add Grand Marnier; reduce by half. Add orange juice. Dissolve arrowroot in chicken stock and add to sauce. Reduce and add honey. Cut segments from fruits and add. Cook for 10 seconds. Pour sauce over veal. Garnish with citrus zest. Makes 2 servings.

title: hearty tuna casserole
directions: Drain and flake the tuna; set aside.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and rinse in hot water.
Combine noodles with the tuna, celery and green onions.
Blend in the sour cream, mustard, mayonnaise, thyme and salt.
Spoon half the mixture into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with half the zucchini.
Repeat layers.
Top with the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle with the chopped tomato.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour, cocoa and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch square pan (greased and floured) for 20 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream and 1/2 envelope taco seasoning.
Brown ground beef and drain. Mix meat with 1 cup water and rest of taco seasoning.
Cook a few minutes, cool and drain. Layer:
cream cheese mixture, meat mixture, shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes, diced peppers and cheeses.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Serve with chips.

title: easy pickled cucumber rounds
directions: Combine first six ingredients in a medium saucepan. Bring mixture to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves. Set aside to cool.

title: nantucket cranberry shortbread
directions: Grease a pie pan. Line with cranberries. Spread the 1/3 cup sugar and 1/3 cup walnuts on top. In a bowl, mix together the next ingredients (sugar, flour, eggs, almond extract and butter). Pour onto the cranberry/sugar walnut mixture in the pie pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is golden.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Make a well
of
the dry ingredients.
Add the eggs and oil, stir
until
everything is moistened.
Stir in the strawberries. Pour
into two 8-inch loaf pans, well-greased.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand to cool.

title: date and nut loaf
directions: Sprinkle soda over cut dates and pour boiling water over both. Stir sugar, butter, salt and egg.
Add nutmeats, date mixture and sifted flour.
Bake in greased loaf pan in slow oven at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: First
Day:
Wash
cucumbers,
put
in large container. Mix salt in a gallon of boiling water and pour over cucumbers. Let stand 24 hours in brine.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in casserole dish.
Drain bacon; leave in frying pan.
Stir in flour, sugar, water and vinegar.
Stir and simmer until it makes a thin sauce.
Add chopped onion and stir. Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Precook the peppers in boiling salted water 5 minutes.
Drain. Cook beef and onion until meat is slightly brown.
Season with salt and a dash of pepper.
Add tomatoes, water, rice and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender. Add cheese. Fill pepper cups and place in baking dish.
Put grated cheese on top and bake, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: savory scallops
directions: Pat dry scallops with paper towel.
Place in greased pie plate. Sprinkle with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Top with mushrooms; drizzle with 1/4 cup butter.
Mix remaining 1/4 cup butter with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over mushrooms.
Broil in preheated broiler 6 inches from heat until scallops are opaque, 10 to 12 minutes. Garnish with parsley.

title: amazing coconut custard pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, Bisquick, eggs, butter and vanilla in a blender.
Cover and blend at low speed for 3 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Pour Doritos in a large bowl and pour chicken broth over them. Let stand 5 minutes; stir occasionally.
Spray large casserole dish with Pam.
Layer 1/3 Doritos, 1/2 green pepper, 1/2 onion, 1/2 chicken and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat.
End with Doritos on top. Reserve 1/3 of cheese.
Mix together soup, tomatoes, garlic salt and chili powder.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: lemon fruit salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and let chill.
Just before serving, add coconut and bananas.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Mix 1 cup of sour cream with cottage cheese. Add onion, Worcestershire sauce and salt to taste.
Mix into noodles and place into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spread with remaining sour cream.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: linguini with clam sauce
directions: Drain broth from clams.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, heat oil and margarine.
Add garlic.
Saute 1 minute.
Sprinkle in flour and cook, stirring constantly 1 minute.
Add clam broth, parsley, salt, pepper and lemon peel.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add clams and heat.
Toss with hot cooked linguini.
Serve with cheese, if desired.
Serves 2 large portions or 4 small side dishes.

title: bacon cheeseburger pizza
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook onion, ground beef and pepper in 8-inch skillet over medium-high heat until meat is no longer pink (8 to 12 minutes).
Drain.
Add pizza sauce.
Reduce heat to low. Cook 5 minutes.
Place baked pizza crust on ungreased 12-inch pizza pan or baking sheet.
Top crust with ground beef mixture, Cheddar cheese, Mozzarella cheese and bacon.
Bake for 8 to 12 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: savory stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat the broiler with the rack on the top shelf of the oven.
Spray a cookie sheet with nonstick spray.
Carefully clean the mushrooms by wiping with a damp paper towel.
Break the stems off and then chop them extremely fine, discarding the tough ends. Heat the oil in a skillet over medium-low heat.
Add the garlic and the chopped stems to the oil.
Fry until the liquid from the mushrooms has evaporated.
Remove from heat and set aside until cool.
Once the stems are cool, stir the cheeses, herbs and spices into the mixture.
The mixture should be thick.
Using a little spoon, fill each mushroom top with a generous amount of the stuffing mixture.
Arrange the mushrooms on the cookie sheet. Bake for about 3 minutes or until sizzling under the broiler.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Mix in eggs, vanilla, flour, soda, salt and oatmeal. Press 2/3 of this dough on cookie sheet. Melt chips, condensed milk, butter and vanilla on low until smooth and creamy. Pour over dough. Arrange remaining dough in little circles on top of chocolate mixture. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Form into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar. Makes 4 dozen.
May be frozen.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water to gelatine.
Mix with other ingredients.
Chill.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix sugars and oil together thoroughly.
Add flour, soda, salt, vanilla and chocolate chips to sugar, oil and egg until well blended.
May use white chocolate chips or peanut butter.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: apricot mochi dessert
directions: Mix together mochi-ko, Jell-O and sugar; stir in nectar and water.
Mix
well.	Pour
into
greased
9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and
cover	tightly
with
foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Keep
foil	on for additional 15 minutes.
Uncover, but cool thoroughly	before	cutting.
Cut into desired shapes or sizes, using
cornstarch
to
coat
lightly in order to handle them without sticking to the dish you wish to set upon.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Soak bread crumbs in
the milk 2 or 3 minutes.
Add all of the remaining
ingredients;
mix
well.
Shape into small 2 ounce round balls and roll in the flour.
Brown in the cooking oil in a frypan.
Remove
from
the
frypan
and
place
in
a roasting pan.
Cover
with
water.
Cook
in preheated oven at 300° for 30 to 40
minutes.
Add
a
small
amount of water if necessary. Makes 8 meat
balls to the pound; this menu should make from 20 to 26 meat balls.

title: broccoli tip salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Then in a small bowl mix the next 3 ingredients very well and pour over the first four ingredients. Double this recipe to serve 9 people.

title: granny's chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in casserole.
Mix soup with 1 cup milk; pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing with 1/2 cup melted butter and broth from chicken.
Spread over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken 'n rice salad
directions: In large bowl, combine rice, chicken, peas, celery and grated onion; set aside.
In another bowl, blend together mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Thoroughly mix into chicken and rice mixture. Chill an hour or more before serving.
Serve on lettuce.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: bake potato bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in pan.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chicken curry
directions: Lightly fry chicken, then remove from frying pan, leaving sufficient cooking oil to lightly fry onions.
Add fried onions and tomatoes to chicken.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Stir cocoa and	baking	soda
in mixing bowl.
Blend in 1/3 cup vegetable
oil, add boiling water; stir in sugar, eggs and remaining 1/3
cup	vegetable oil;	stir until smooth. Add flour, vanilla
and salt, blend completely.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x
9-inch
baking
pan
or	two 8-inch square pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes for 13 x 9-inch pan or 30 to 32 minutes for 8-inch pans.
Cool;
frost if desired.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Do this first!
Separate the whites of eggs; beat very stiff; beat in sugar and stir in pecans and chocolate bits.
Cover cookie sheet with foil and spoon the mixture onto the cookie sheet.
Put in the oven and turn the oven off.
The next morning, you will have your Forgotten Cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute chopped onions and celery.
Place in a casserole dish and then layer the chicken, soup and stuffing.
Season with salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Pour the chicken broth over top and bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: festive punch
directions: Chill ingredients.
Combine in punch bowl.
Float ice mold in punch when ready to serve.

title: cherry bing bars
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Crush peanuts fine and add with Rice Krispies to chocolate.
Mix well and put in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pennsylvania dutch lettuce
directions: Cook bacon until crisp. Combine egg, onion, sugar, salt, vinegar and water. Add to bacon and stir. Heat to boiling. Pour hot dressing over lettuce and toss.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat slowly the milk, egg yolks and lemon juice.
Wash beaters.
Now, beat the egg whites slowly, adding 2 tablespoons of sugar per egg white.
Pour lemon mixture into baked pie shell. Top with egg white mixture.
Brown in 400° oven.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Put the noodles in bottom of a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Brown the hamburger with the onion. Spread over the noodles.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Cook sausage in skillet until brown and crisp.
Drain fat. Heat 2 tablespoons sausage drippings in skillet and saute onion until tender.
Set aside.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook hamburger and onion.
Drain butter and lima beans; mix meat, beans and other vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: swiss carrot cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat sugar, oil and butter.
With beater at low speed, add sifted dry ingredients alternating with eggs, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add carrots, nuts and pineapple.
Grease 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crescent dinner rolls
directions: Stir up and let set overnight (covered).
Divide into thirds. Roll out as pie dough.
Cut into 8 equal parts.
(I use pizza cutter.)
Let rise again, 6 to 8 hours.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: sesame teriyaki bites
directions: Cut steak into 24 cubes.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
Combine juice, teriyaki sauce, honey and ground ginger. Marinate steak in mixture overnight.

title: tutti-frutti milk shake
directions: Measure all ingredients into blender.
Blend for approximately 1 minute.
Drink immediately.
Serves 2.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans and peas.
Mix all ingredients together.
Stir well and let chill at least 1 hour.
Better if chilled overnight.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add other ingredients. Cook thirty minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium, cooking, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
It's done!

title: lemon bars
directions: Crust:
Combine 1/2 cup margarine, 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup powdered sugar.
Cut fine with pastry blender.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan.
Press on bottom until spread flat all over.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
This should not be brown.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Combine milk and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; boil for 4 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly.
In bowl place chocolate chips, milk chocolate bar, marshmallow cream and nuts.
Pour hot sugar mixture over top and stir until all is mixed.
Put into buttered pan to cool.
Let set before cutting.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough onto a sound pizza pan and bake at 350° until golden brown, about 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Spread cream cheese on cooled cookie dough and layer sliced fruit, arranging like a pizza.

title: mexican vegetable dip
directions: Combine olive oil, vinegar, garlic salt and pepper to taste in bowl; mix well.
Add chopped vegetables; mix well.
Chill overnight.
Stir to mix.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 96 tablespoons.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sour cream, oregano and garlic powder. Spread evenly in a 9 or 10 inch pie plate. Spread pizza sauce over the top. Sprinkle with pepperoni, onion and green pepper. Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes. Top with cheese and bake for 5 minutes more until heated through. Serve with crackers, vegetables or chips.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Add oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla and milk. Mix in dry ingredients.
Stir in zucchini and chocolate chips. Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan (Pam sprayed if preferred).
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix well.
Shape into 2 ounce balls.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve with your favorite sauce.

title: chinese cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage in small amount of salted water for 5 minutes and drain.
Saute all vegetables, except cabbage, in butter.
Butter a baking dish and layer cabbage and then vegetables until all are used.

title: date pudding
directions: Boil 3 minutes; put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix syrup and sugar well.
Cook at High power in microwave oven for 4 minutes. Then add peanuts and cook 3 minutes.
Then add butter and vanilla; cook for 1 minute.
Add soda and mix well, then pour in an ungreased cookie sheet.
Let harden.

title: steak and ale sauteed mushrooms
directions: Wash and trim mushrooms; dice.
Boil in water to cover, 5 minutes.
Drain.
Melt oleo in pot and saute onions.
Add mushrooms, beef bouillon cubes, cornstarch and seasonings.
Mix until dissolved.
Add wine and Worcestershire and simmer until mushrooms are tender (20 to 30 minutes).

title: cheesy broccoli 'n mushroom bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange broccoli in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix well.
Grease cookie sheet with sides; line with waxed paper.
Grease paper; pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn cake upside-down on cloth tea towel dusted with 10x sugar.
Pull off paper.
Roll tight and cool.
Unroll and fill with filling.

title: deer jerky
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Cut meat into thin strips; soak in mixture overnight in refrigerator, covered.
Put toothpicks through the end of each slice and hang on oven rack.
Cook at 150° for 4 to 7 hours with oven door slightly ajar.
Bake according to how chewy or crispy you want.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Stir in gelatin; add pineapple and mix well. Chill.
When mixture begins to thicken, fold in whipped topping. Pour into a 2 1/2-quart serving bowl.
Chill for at least 2 hours.

title: garlic bread
directions: Heat the oven to 375°. Halve the bread lengthwise. In a small bowl, stir the oil, oregano, garlic and pepper. Spread on bread. Wrap each half in foil, leaving the tops uncovered. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 25 minutes until golden and crusted. With a serrated knife, cut each half into 6 pieces. Serves 6.

title: grandma flo's lemon pie
directions: In small saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch, salt, lemon juice and water.
Cook until thick.
Add a little of this mixture into beaten egg yolks.
Then place into saucepan and cook 2 more minutes. Place into a baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon pie salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in 2 cups hot water. Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water. Mix together.
Add pineapple and juice.
Chill until thick.
Beat with mixer.
Beat in Cool Whip and lemon pie filling. Top with nuts or grated cheese.

title: "brunch" cheesecake(makes 16 to 20 servings)
directions: In a small bowl, dissolve yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in warm milk; let stand until foamy (5 to 10 minutes).
In a large bowl, combine flour and salt.
With pastry blender, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add 4 egg yolks to yeast mixture and stir until blended.
Stir into flour mixture until well blended; set aside.

title: orange sherbet-gelatin salad
directions: Add sherbet into dissolved gelatin in boiling water.
Mix well.
When partially set (about 5 minutes), add orange slices and Cool Whip.
Fold in and refrigerate.

title: crabbies appetizer
directions: Mix margarine, mayo, cheese and garlic salt.
Mashing with a fork, add crabmeat.
Spread on 12 English muffin halves.
Cut into quarters or smaller.

title: tuna burger
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Fill buns, wrap each in foil.
Put in 250° oven for 20 minutes.
Enjoy.
Can use chicken in place of tuna.

title: venison jerky
directions: Cut venison into strips about 1/2-inch thick, 1-inch wide and 12-inches long.
Dig a 3-foot square hole about 3-feet deep.
Make a narrow ditch from the side down into the bottom of the hole to produce an oxygen supply when a fire is built in the hole.
Build a slow fire in the hole.
Put green lengths of small branches over the hole and lay the strips of meat over these.
Cover this over with logs or anything available, but leave enough of an opening so the fire will not go out.
Keep the slow smoldering fire going for about 12 hours by dropping in small pieces of dry wood.
Jerky will keep almost indefinitely.
It may be soaked in water 4 or 5 hours and boiled into a stew.

title: dumplings, pork hocks and kraut
directions: Combine all dry ingredients, then add beaten egg, milk and shortening.
Mix well and form into balls.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Mix dry ingredients. Stir in	milk
and
mix	thoroughly.
Add
to
melted
butter. Arrange 2 cups
fruit
in batter.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over top.
Bake 15	minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350°.	Bake 20 minutes more or until golden brown.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix together Oreo cookies and melted butter. Spread mixture in the bottom of a cake pan.
Place in freezer to stiffen.
In the same bowl, mix together Cool Whip, cream cheese and vanilla.
Spread over cookie mixture.
Top with chocolate pudding.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: oatmeal squares
directions: Bring sugar, butter, cocoa and milk to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and pour in a dish.

title: blt dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Refrigerate for 1 hour. Serve with ritz crackers.

title: ina lou hurt's chess pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add eggs and milk and beat until sugar is almost dissolved.
Add melted butter, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour in uncooked pie shell and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until firm.

title: lania's best pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream margarine and cream cheese, add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat only until mixed well.
Add flour, about 1/2 cup at a time, scraping down sides as they need it.
Add vanilla.
Beat on low to medium speed, about 1 to 2 minutes until smooth.
Pour into greased tube or Bundt pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown and done.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Pour hot water over gelatin and stir well.
Add pineapple, cherries and nuts.
Pour in Coca-Cola and stir well.
Let set overnight.

title: depression era pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into two 9-inch unbaked pie shells.
Bake in
a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Tastes like pecan pie.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Boil in microwave - butter with 1 cup water then add flour. Mix well to form a ball.
Cool for 5 minutes then add eggs, one at a time.
Spread in a well greased 9x13 pan.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: autumn soup
directions: Stew and debone chicken.
Add remaining ingredients to water reserved from stewing chicken.
Cut chicken into bite-size chunks. Add to soup.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: nite night cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites.
Gradually fold in sugar.
Add cream of tartar; beat, then fold in chocolate chips. On 2 cookie sheets, lay wax paper.
Drop mixture onto wax paper by spoonfuls.
Put pans into oven.
Count to 10. Turn oven off. Leave cookies in oven 6 to 8 hours or overnight.

title: holiday yams
directions: Combine sugar and starch. Blend well. Stir in liquid, butter and salt. Simmer over low heat, stirring constantly, until begins to thicken. Place yams in lightly greased 2-quart casserole. Add sauce. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: rhubarb kuchen
directions: Combine gelatin, 1/3 cup of sugar, 3 tablespoons of flour and rhubarb; mix well.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: irresistible chocolate chip cookies
directions: Soak raisins in rum for 60 minutes (optional).
In a large bowl, cream butter.
Add sugars and cream again until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla until smooth.
In a separate bowl, mix dry ingredients (flour, oatmeal, salt and baking soda). Add dry mixture to other bowl and mix well.
Now add chocolate chips, nuts and raisins.
Stir from the bottom of the bowl until all the ingredients are well combined.
Preheat oven to 350°. Drop by teaspoons onto well-buttered cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on racks.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9-inch or 10-inch tube pan.
Mix together the 4 teaspoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon and set aside.

title: potatoes anna
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Using 3 tablespoons of butter or margarine grease a heavy 8-inch skillet.
Peel potatoes.
Cut potatoes crosswise into thin slices.
Put potatoes in a large bowl and toss gently with salt and pepper.
Arrange in layers covering with butter.
Place skillet over medium-high heat and cook 3 minutes to brown the bottom of potatoes.
Remove from heat and cover with foil.
Press down firmly with 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Place skillet and dish in center of rack in oven.
Bake 30 minutes. Remove Pyrex dish and foil; bake 5 more minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
In large Dutch oven, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover.
Bake for 6 to 7 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaves.
Makes 12 (1 cup) servings.

title: scrumptious shrimp dip
directions: Finely chop the top ends of the scallions.
Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Mix softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and scallions.
Add drained cans of shrimp.
Squeeze juice from lemon.
Add Worcestershire sauce and salt and pepper to taste.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and put half of crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Mix in confectioners sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: salmon patties
directions: Debone salmon.
Add eggs, flour, meal, ketchup and onions. Slowly add enough milk to make batter that can be dropped into grease.
Heat Teflon pan to medium.
Drop patties by the spoonful into butter flavored Crisco.
Cook until golden brown.

title: scalloped corn with jiffy mix
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Add thawed strawberries, nuts, pineapple and mashed bananas. Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour half of mixture into 8 x 12 pan. Place in refrigerator until set (about 15 minutes). Spread sour cream over set jello and then add remaining mixture to top of sour cream. Let it set in refrigerator about 30 minutes. Cut in squares to serve. Makes about 12 servings.

title: barazushi
directions: Cook 4 cups rice.
Soak Kurome in water; drain when soft.
Cook grated carrot, Aburage, kamaboko, Takemoto, Kurome and ajisukekogai together with Wesson oil, shoyu, sugar and sake.
Set aside until rice is done.
Add 1 package Tamanoi sushi rice mix to hot rice; mix all together with the cooked ingredients.
Garnish with thinly sliced eggs and red and green shrimp flakes.
Delicious hot or cold.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake covered in casserole dish for 60 minutes at 350°.

title: cake cookies
directions: *Lemon cake mix and strawberry work well for these cookies.

title: banana blueberry pie
directions: Bake 2 pie shells.
Cool.
Mix together Cool Whip, softened cream cheese and sugar.
Cut up 3 bananas and fold into mixture. Divide into 2 pie shells.
Top with blueberry filling; refrigerate.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut lettuce and cauliflower into pieces.
Layer ingredients in order listed.
Store covered in refrigerator about 12 hours.
Toss and serve.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef and onion in small amount of fat. Mix with remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes. Serve on heated hamburger buns. Serves 4 to 5 generously.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown beef, then brown onions and pepper.
Mix chili powder, salt and pepper.
Grease casserole dish; add rice.
Pour mixture into dish.
Cover with grated cheese (optional).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: mom piper's chocolate cake
directions: Measure all dry ingredients except cocoa into mixing bowl. Add eggs, oil and milk to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
In a saucepan, mix cocoa and boiling water.
Add vanilla and blend well.
Blend cocoa mixture into ingredients in mixing bowl. Batter will be thin.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and frost with fluffy icing.

title: karo classic pecan pie
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients until blended.
Add nuts. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: If using frozen mixed vegetables, cook, then drain.
Combine first 6 ingredients.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: meat and vegetable pie
directions: In medium bowl, mix flour and salt.
Cut in lard or shortening until small particles are formed.
Mixing with fork, gradually stir in 5 tablespoons cold water or enough to hold particles together.
Form into a ball and wrap in plastic.
Chill while preparing filling.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients at one time, except nuts and apples.
Mix well.
(Omit baking powder if using self-rising flour.)
Fold in nuts and apples.
Bake in 12-cup tube pan at 350° for 1 hour. Let stand awhile before turning out.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Drop
by teaspoon into a mixture of cinnamon and sugar. Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Lightly brown chicken breasts in 2 tablespoons of the margarine, seasoning to taste with salt and pepper. If serving in individual casseroles, arrange 2 pieces of broccoli in each, end to end, with buds towards outside of dish. Arrange chicken over broccoli.

title: cherry pie delight
directions: Mix flour, eggs and sugar together.
Spread cherry pie filling in greased cake pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon over cherries.
Spread flour mixture over cherries.
Pour butter over flour mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: stuffed cabbage casserole
directions: Place cabbage in greased baking dish.
Brown meat and onion. Stir in rice.
Cook until rice is brown.
Pour mixture over cabbage.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix soup and water in bowl.
Pour over cabbage.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
In separate saucepan boil 1 cup water and add bouillon cube.
Break up noodles and slightly brown in the butter.
Stir constantly.
Add rice and saute a few minutes, stirring.
Add beef broth.
Cover and cook on low fire 20 minutes.
When water is absorbed and rice is soft, remove from fire and let stand 15 minutes with napkin undercover.
Stir and serve.
Serves 2.

title: raisin orange bread
directions: Combine raisins and water; bring to boil.
Cool to room temperature.
Mix egg, brown sugar, salad oil and orange peel. Stir in raisin mixture.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and soda; add, beating well.
Pour into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf dish.
Bake at 325° for about 60 minutes.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet and add vegetables; saute until tender.
Stir in herbs and spices.
In large bowl, blend eggs and cheese and add vegetable mixture.

title: egg salad
directions: Combine the eggs, scallions, celery, caraway seed and bacon. Toss lightly. Combine the mayonnaise and horseradish; fold the mixture into the salad. Sprinkle with parsley and serve. Serves 4.

title: hot tamale casserole
directions: Boil ground chuck 45 minutes, salt water to taste.
Crumble chuck up real fine as it cooks.
Drain the water from the meat, saving it for later.

title: cookie pie
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add juice and mix well.
Bring to a boil. Add jello to boiling mixture.
Cool completely.
Beat chilled milk until foamy.
Pour in jello mixture while mixing.
Line 2 pie plates with vanilla wafers.
Chill until ready to serve.
You may use different flavors of jello.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms; remove stems.
Lay caps upside down in greased baking dish.
Chop stems.
In skillet, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Add mushroom stems and saute.
Combine stems and remaining butter, pecans, onions, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Fill each cap with a teaspoon of the butter mixture.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes until bubbly.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes into thick crosswise slices.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Coat tomatoes with dry mixture.
Drop in hot oil until golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chinese broccoli and beef salad
directions: Cut florets off broccoli; reserve tender parts of stalks. Cut stalks into 3/8-inch thick slices.
In wok or large skillet, heat oil and stir-fry stalks for 1 minute.
Add florets and stir-fry for 3 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Transfer broccoli to large bowl.
Stir-fry pepper strips for 1/2 minute; add to broccoli.
Stir-fry mushrooms until crisp-tender; add to broccoli. Combine vinegar, soy sauce, salt and red pepper.
Pour over broccoli mixture; toss well.
Add beef, water chestnuts and bamboo shoots.
Toss.
Cover and chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Makes 12 servings.

title: honey of a ham steak
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place ham steak in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour milk over ham.
Combine mustard and honey, spread on top of ham.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cut into 4 pieces.
Serves 4.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Wash shrimp; drain and dry.
Place shrimp in roasting pan. Spread butter over shrimp completely.
Cover buttered shrimp with lots of black pepper so all you can see is pepper about 1/8-inch thick.
Cover.
Bake about 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve with lots of French bread for dipping in butter sauce.

title: quick creamed chicken
directions: In hot butter in skillet, saute green pepper until tender. Stir in soup and milk.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly.
Then add chicken and pimento.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Serve over toast.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion.
Boil for 5 minutes and drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots.
Fold in squash and onion. Combine stuffing mix and butter.

title: hobo stew
directions: Brown hamburger in large pot.
Pour off excess fat.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: baked butter beans
directions: Drain beans and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix in tomato sauce, brown sugar, salt, mustard and syrup.
Mix flour in water to dissolve and stir into bean mixture.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours or until it thickens.

title: yuletide dessert
directions: Mix cookies and 1/3 cup butter to make crumbs.
Press in bottom of pan; reserve 2 tablespoons for topping.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Spread over crumbs.
Whip 1 cup cream and add 4 cups sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, 1/2 cup chopped walnuts, 1 ripe banana (mashed) and 1/4 cup maraschino cherries.
Pile on top.
Scatter reserved crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.
Ready to serve.

title: vidalia pie(hot appetizer)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix well; put in greased dish and bake 25 - 30 minutes.

title: sausage-potato-dinner
directions: Grease a 10-inch baking dish.
Line the bottom with potatoes. In separate saucepan, heat soup and water, stirring until smooth. Stir in cheese until melted.
Add Hillshire sausage pieces, green pepper and pimento (if desired).
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange balls (no bake)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into bite size balls.
Reserve several spoons of powdered sugar.
Place in a small bag and add balls and shake.
If you like coconut, roll balls in flaked coconut instead of using powdered sugar.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Take chicken off the bone.
Mix flour, butter and eggs together.
Roll out and cut into strips. Put chicken and strips of noodles into pot together.
Fill with water until all is covered.
Cook until noodles are soft.

title: broccoli-cheddar squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix broccoli, corn, onion and walnuts; place in pan.
Beat remaining ingredients except cheese until smooth.
Pour evenly into pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until a knife in center comes out clean; then sprinkle and top with cheese.
Bake another 5 minutes. Let cool; then cut into squares.
Top each square with a sliced black olive.

title: lulu's potato salad dressing
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk and vinegar slowly.
Stir constantly while cooking until mixture thickens.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet. Add mushrooms, flour, salt and paprika. Stir in soup. Cook slowly, about 20 minutes, stirring frequently. Add sour cream and cook for about 8 minutes. Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour additional butter on top and bake for 15 more minutes to brown. Serve warm or cool.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding whipped cream last.
Chill.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter and oil on medium-high.
Add flour to thicken.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Place meat in deep roaster.
Add water and cook until tender enough to shred meat into bite size pieces.
Then add diced onion and celery.
Put all three back into roaster.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer about 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheddar parmesan potatoes
directions: Melt butter over low heat in a saucepan.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add salt and cheeses.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add potatoes.
Stir gently to mix.
Place in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add shortening and eggs and mix until well blended.
Stir in vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8-10 minutes at 350 degrees.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onion with the water in a covered pan until tender.
Do not drain.
Add milk, bouillon cubes and butter.
Mix sour cream with flour until smooth.
Add to soup and cook it until thick, stirring constantly.
Add salt and pepper. Add ham, if desired.

title: doughnuts
directions: Cream the butter; add sugar gradually and cream until light. Stir in beaten eggs.
Add flour, baking powder and salt to the creamed mixture alternately with the milk.
Stir in vanilla. Chill the dough for several hours.
Roll out 1/3-inch thick on a floured surface.
Cut with a floured cutter.
Fry in deep fat (375°) until golden brown.
Turn.
Drain on a paper towel.
Cover with cinnamon or powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar, syrup and butter.
Let boil for 30 minutes.
Stir often so it won't scorch.
Let cool and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until it thickens about 10 minutes. Pour into greased pan and let sit.

title: cheesy bacon bites
directions: Combine cream cheese, bacon, onion and pepper.
Separate crescent rolls into two rectangles; pinch seams together.
Spread cheese mixture on each rectangle.
Roll up starting at longest side and seal.
Cut each roll into 16 slices.
For easier cutting, I roll in wax paper and chill for a few minutes prior to slicing. Place slices, cut side down, on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: Make into balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Press in bottom of 9 x 12-inch dish; cook at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into large baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Put boneless, skinless chicken breasts on top of rice mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: smoky salmon spread
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 2 teaspoons liquid, and flake. Combine cream cheese, liquid smoke and salmon liquid; blend thoroughly.
Stir in green onion, then fold in salmon. Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight to blend flavors. Serve as a spread with crackers.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups spread.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Press in a cookie sheet the margarine, oatmeal, brown sugar, flour and nuts.
Cook in a 400° oven.
Watch it until brown; crumble while hot.
Put 1/2 in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Gently push it down.
Drizzle a little caramel sauce on crumbs.
Put softened ice cream over caramel sauce, the rest of crumbs over that and drizzle a little more caramel sauce over top.
Cover; put in freezer.

title: easy strawberry tart(very easy & quick)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: orange coffee punch
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Blend together milk, coffee, sugar and orange extract.
Pour into chilled punch bowl and top with small scoops of sherbet.
Yields 4 2/3 cups.

title: banana split cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick melted oleo and 1/2 cup sugar.
Press crumbs into pan and bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix softened butter and flour; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans and press into dough.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: french onion beef stew
directions: Dust beef with flour; place in dish.
Add potatoes, onions, celery and carrots.
Combine tomato juice, sugar, sauce, salt, pepper and basil.
Pour over beef and vegetables.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: peel off pounds soup
directions: Cut vegetables in medium size pieces.
Cover with water and boil for 10 minutes.
Lower heat.
Add soup mix and simmer until vegetables are soft.

title: cheese cake
directions: Thoroughly butter the bottom and sides of a 9-inch square metal cake pan. Pour the graham cracker crumbs in the baking pan; insure that all surfaces are coated with the crumbs. Turn pan over an tap lightly to release excess crumbs.

title: cheese and pasta in a pot
directions: Cook
macaroni
and
set aside.
Saute onion and garlic until soft,
then
brown beef in same skillet.
When browned, drain all fat and juices.
Meat mixture should be dry.

title: cherry-chocolate oatmeal bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease jellyroll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Mix sugar, butter, almond extract and eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Stir in oats. Reserve 1/3 of oats mixture.
Press remaining mixture in pan.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a bowl. Serve in a bowl or dish using paprika on top for garnish. Serve with vegetable slices, crackers, chips or bread.

title: texas brownies
directions: Use a large mixing bowl.
Combine the flour and the sugar in a heavy saucepan.
Combine butter, shortening and coffee or water. Pour boiling mixture over.
Add the buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well using a wooden spoon or high speed of electric mixer.
Pour into a well buttered 17 1/2 x 11-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brownies are done in center.
While brownies are baking, prepare frosting.

title: turkey salad burritos
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine turkey, celery, onion, black olives and cheese.
In another bowl, whisk together salad dressing, picante sauce and salt.
Pour sauce over turkey mixture; blend well.
Spoon filling onto tortillas; wrap burrito-style.* Heat in 13 x 9 x 3-inch baking pan at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly warmed or microwave each burrito 2 to 2 1/2 minutes on High.
Serve with additional picante sauce; garnish with black olives.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: french mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water 25 to 30 minutes. Drain and mash.
Add milk, butter, seasonings and baking powder. Beat until fluffy.
Add onion.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350° or 375°.

title: oatmeal carrot cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream together margarine, brown sugar and white sugar; blend in egg.
Add carrots and vanilla; mix well.
In a separate bowl, combine dry ingredients (flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and cloves).
Add flour mixture, alternating with oatmeal to cream mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in raisins.
Drop dough by teaspoon on cookie sheet coated with vegetable spray.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: stuffed eggplant italiano
directions: Cut eggplant in half, lengthwise.
Place halves, cut side down, in shallow baking pan. Bake at 350° about 15 minutes. Remove from oven. Cool slightly. Scoop out pulp, leaving 3/8-inch shell. Place shells, cut side up, in baking pan.
Coarsely chop pulp. Combine with remaining ingredients except Mozzarella cheese. Fill eggplant shells, pressing firmly.
Cover with foil.
Pierce foil in several places to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Remove foil and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, uncovered, about 2 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Cut each half into 2 pieces to serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cinnamon coffee bars
directions: Cream together thoroughly the shortening, brown sugar and egg. Stir in the hot coffee.
Sift together all the remaining dry ingredients.
Blend in nuts.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch oblong pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Frost while still warm with a thin coating of Quick Coffee Cream Icing.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: white cream sauce for scallops and shrimp
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour over low heat.
Gradually add milk and water.
Heat slowly until it boils and thickens.
Stir in cheese and basil.
Add pepper to taste.
Serve over linguini with fresh scallops and shrimp.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop everything as small as possible; mix well.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Makes 1 large or 2 smaller balls.

title: quick cottage cheese salad
directions: Sprinkle Jell-O over cottage cheese; mix well. Add pineapple, oranges and rice. Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: wild cherry wine
directions: Put all cherries through meat grinder, then add water and sugar.
Ferment in stoneware container for 20 days.
Strain; add more sugar if needed. Ferment for another 3 weeks before serving.

title: mock eclair cake
directions: In bottom of pan place one layer of graham crackers.
Make pudding according to directions.
Mix Cool Whip in with pudding. Pour 1/2 on top of graham crackers.
Place next layer of graham crackers.
Pour rest of pudding on 2nd layer of graham crackers. Place graham crackers on top.
Stir icing and spread on top of crackers.
Best if chilled for 15 minutes before serving.

title: chicken wings
directions: Cut wings at joint.
Wash.
Pat dry on paper towel.
Combine remaining ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange wings in single layer in marinade.
Cover.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven until tender, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick taco dip
directions: Layer ingredients, cheese on the bottom, chili and cheese. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In a pan bring the water, cocoa, oil and margarine to a boil. Add the flour, sugar, salt, eggs, vanilla, milk and baking soda. Pour onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
As soon as cake is done ice with the following icing.

title: quick sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix catsup or chili sauce, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over hamburger and onion.
Simmer a few minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together except pecans.
Roll it into a ball; chilled for a couple of hours.
Roll it in the pecans.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll each in additional sugar, then bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Gently press an unwrapped Hershey's Kiss into each ball.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Chop half of the mushrooms.
In a large bowl, combine chopped mushrooms, ground beef, 1/4 cup of soup, egg, 2 tablespoons of milk, bread crumbs, onion and pepper.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High for 9 to 10 minutes.
Drain and let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in graham cracker crust. Refrigerate.

title: all in one casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In medium saucepan, bring water and butter to a boil. Add milk and instant potatoes. Stir and set aside. In large skillet, brown beef and onions. Drain off fat. Add soup, beans and seasonings, except paprika; stir thoroughly. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Top with potatoes. Sprinkle paprika over top for garnish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pecan cream cheese pie
directions: In a small bowl, beat together the cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar, 1 egg, 1 teaspoon vanilla and the salt until thick, creamy and smooth.
Reserve.
In another small bowl, beat 3 eggs just until yolks and whites are combined.
Add the corn syrup, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat gently until blended.
Spread reserved cream cheese mixture in the bottom of unbaked pie shell; sprinkle with the pecans and gently pour the syrup mixture over the pecans.
Bake at 375° until the center is firm to the touch, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: sausage jambalaya(club member: nicholas)
directions: Place 2 tablespoons oil in saucepan. Add sausage and brown. Add onions and garlic. Cook until tender. Add water, red pepper, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Add rice and bell pepper. When rice starts to swell, turn gently. Cover pot and cook on low heat until rice is tender, 15 or 20 minutes.

title: minced clam casserole
directions: Bake in 375° oven, 1/2 hour or until golden brown.
If too moist, add more crackers.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese and butter.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Frost between layers, top and sides.

title: doritos and fritos dish
directions: Reserve some of the chips and cheese for topping. Mix all other ingredients together. Top with the saved cheese and chips. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tenn trash
directions: Mix popped corn, cereals and nuts in roaster pan.
Cook brown sugar, margarine and Karo.
Cook until comes to a boil.
Stirring constantly, let boil 5 minutes.
Not stirring, removing and add vanilla and soda.
Pour over dry mixture.
Cook for 45 minutes at 350°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: roast chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Place the bay leaf, thyme and garlic in the cavity of the chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and then truss.
Place chicken in roasting pan; scatter onion chunks around it.
Rub with olive oil.
Place the chicken on its side and bake for 20 minutes.
Occasionally, pour off fat.
Place chicken on its back.
Add margarine and chicken broth and roast 20 minutes longer, continuing to baste.
It is done when juice is clear.

title: quinoam, leek and tofu casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Working with 1/2 cup tofu at a time, squeeze out water with hands.
Set aside.
Heat a large skillet or wok; add oil.
Add garlic, then leek.
Saute until lightly browned.
Add quinoa, then tofu, sauteing for 2 minutes after each addition.
Add seasonings.
Oil casserole.
Add 1/2 cup bread crumbs; rotate casserole to coat evenly.
Gently add the quinoa mixture.
Press a well in the center of the quinoa; pour in soymilk.
Cover with remaining bread crumbs and cheese.
Cover; bake for 20 minutes.
Remove cover; continue to bake until cheese is nicely browned.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Serve with your choice of vegetables.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix cake mix (as it comes from box) with remaining ingredients with a spoon.
Pour into a very lightly greased jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 12 1/2-inch).
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven, then cool.
Ice with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In 13 x 9-inch square cake pan or casserole dish, lay in peaches (drain peaches).
Put juice in large saucepan.
Add vanilla flavor, oleo and cinnamon.
Cook over low heat.
Stir.
Add cornstarch.
Dissolve about 10 minutes.
Pour over peaches.
Lay pie crust on wax paper.
Cut in strips.
Lay on top of peaches. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together for dressing.
Toss salad ingredients with dressing.
Chill for two hours before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Wash and scrape carrots; cut in diagonal slices.
Cook, covered, in small amount of water until just tender (approximately 12 minutes).
Drain.
Heat margarine, sugar and preserves in saucepan, stirring to combine.
Stir into carrots until coated. Cook over low heat, stirring gently about 3 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix chicken broth that is thickened.
Combine the mayonnaise, lemon juice and cheese.
Pour mixture over chicken and rice.
Add bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: my moms fruit salad
directions: Chop unpeeled apples into 1/2 inch chunks. Slice banana into 1/4 inch slices and split all grapes in half. Mix jello according to box directions in a 2 quart casserole dish. Add all remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly. Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, salt and flour.
Add milk and water. Microwave
for 3 minutes on High; stir.
If it is not thick enough, heat for 2 more minutes.
Add egg yolks and heat 3 more minutes.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Stir and pour into cooked pie shell.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until stiff.
Add sugar slowly.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet covered with aluminum foil.
Place in 350° preheated oven.
Turn off and leave overnight.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine milk and water; heat in large saucepan.
Add meal, sugar and salt, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add and mix well egg and margarine.
Pour into greased pan and bake for 1 hour at 400° or until golden brown.
May substitute artificial sweetener for diabetics.

title: orange-apricot salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boil.
Add sugar and jello powder.
Stir. Add cream cheese.
Cook and stir until cream cheese melts.
Add apricots.
Pour into bowl.
Partially chill.
Add Cool Whip. Stir.
Chill in mold until set.

title: cassions dressing
directions: Dissolve sugar and oil.
Add wine vinegar; heat, then cool. Add dry mustard and salt; beat until creamy.
Add onion and celery seed.
Beat again and chill.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Pour 1/2 gallon boiling water over 1 quart capped and washed strawberries; drain well.

title: tuna ball(roll)
directions: Blend 2 tablespoons of parsley with remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Place in refrigerator until very cold.
Turn out onto waxed paper.
Shape into ball or 2 rolls.
Roll in remaining parsley.
This freezes well so can be made ahead of time.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Then fold in Cool Whip and crushed pineapple (not drained).
Pour into graham cracker crust and place in refrigerator and let chill from 30 to 45 minutes before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Peel and devein shrimp, leaving tail intact.
Preheat oven. Melt butter and rest of ingredients, except shrimp.
Place shrimp in shallow baking dish, tail up.
Pour sauce over all. Bake 5 minutes. Place under broiler 5 minutes to brown.
Serve over rice.

title: ham and cheese strada
directions: Butter a 3-quart baking dish (9 x 13-inch) Butter one side of 8 slices of bread.
Place buttered side down in baking dish.
Spread with mustard.
Top bread with cheese slices.
Sprinkle with white or green onions.
Top with ham slices.
Butter remaining 8 slices of bread.
Place over ham, buttered side up.
Beat milk, eggs, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over bread.
Pat down.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour (longer if very cold when placed in oven).
Serves 8.

title: hill billy black-eyed peas
directions: Cook peas until tender.
Place onion, Worcestershire sauce and butter in with ham and peas.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: cheese roll
directions: Let cheese soften.
Roll out Velveeta on wax paper to thin layer.
Spread cream cheese on Velveeta.
Chop pepper into small pieces.
Sprinkle on cream cheese.
Mince green onions and sprinkle over peppers.
Last, sprinkle garlic salt over entire mixture. Starting at one end, roll up jelly roll style.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate overnight.
Slice to serve.

title: cajun seasoning mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl; mix thoroughly.
Store in tightly covered glass jar for use as needed.

title: leek and sweet pepper toss
directions: In a microwave, melt margarine in a small dish for 20 seconds on High.
Add pepper, leek, stock and thyme.
Cover with vented plastic wrap; microwave on High until vegetables are tender, about 3 minutes.
Toss with cooked broccoli or other vegetables; sprinkle on cheese.
Serve warm as a side dish or tossed with hot pasta as an entree.
Serves 4.

title: breakfast slush
directions: Chase wild bullfrogs for 3 miles to gather up hops.
To them, add 10 gallons of tan bark, 1/2 pint of shellac and 1 bar of homemade soap.
Boil 36 hours.
Strain through one well worn sock to keep it from working.
Add one grasshopper to each pint to give it a kick.
Pour a little into the kitchen sink.
If it takes the enamel off, it's ready to bottle.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart baking pan.
Stir. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Top with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: marinated cucumber salad
directions: Mix Italian sauce, sugar, water, black pepper, vinegar, salad oil and salt.
Pour over vegetables; cover.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.
Drain.
Serve in lettuce lined bowl.
Makes 8 servings.

title: james italian  meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Form into about 1 inch balls and place on lightly greased baking sheet.

title: stewed tomato casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Stir in bread cubes until slightly brown and toasted; set aside.

title: old fashioned biscuits
directions: Blend flour, salt, sugar and baking powder. Cut in shortening until crumbly. Combine milk and 1/4 cup ice water. Add all at once to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Knead dough. Roll out and cut into biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: nutty dumplings
directions: Arrange pineapple slices in 10-inch skillet with cover.
Pour in syrup from fruit and heat.
Combine biscuit mix, milk, nuts and 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Mix well with a fork.
Spoon on pineapple slices and cook on low heat about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle brown sugar over the top and cook another 10 minutes.

title: chicken delight
directions: Lay chicken in a well-greased glass dish (9 x 12) and put one piece of cheese on each piece of chicken.

Warm milk and soup; pour over chicken. Melt margarine and add stuffing. Sprinkle over soup/chicken. Cover with tinfoil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Take off foil and let brown 15 minutes more. Can be prepared night before and then cooked day to be served.

title: salsa
directions: Put into large bowl and blend with hand blender (or food processor).
Put into sealable container and chill.
Will stay fresh for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: rum cake and coffee
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Place chopped pecans in bottom (if like, chopped cherries).
Mix all ingredients well (can be slightly lumpy).
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Remove cake from oven, leave in pan and add glaze.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Beat together shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolk and vanilla. Stir in flour; fold in potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: To 2 cups medium white cream sauce, add 1/2 cup sour cream, 2 tablespoons prepared mustard and 1 tablespoon prepared horseradish.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion, celery and pepper.
Cover and cook until tender.
Add mushrooms and cook for 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes and salt, sugar and garlic powder to taste.
Simmer all together, stirring and breaking up the tomatoes for 5 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together chicken, soup, water chestnuts, mushrooms, mayonnaise, onion, celery and sour cream.
Line bottom of 8 x 13-inch baking dish with rice.
Pour chicken mixture over top. Top with Crescent rolls like crust.
Drizzle with butter, top with cheese and almonds.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: christmas cheese ball
directions: Mix equal amounts of cream cheese and Cheddar cheese. Roll into log or ball. Place line of chili powder on wax paper and roll. Sprinkle top with chives, paprika and pepper.

title: beef broccoli supper
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in a large skillet, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink; drain.
Add the rice, broccoli, soup, milk, seasoning blend, salt and pepper; stir until combined.
Transfer to a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Toss bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over beef mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake 5 to 10 minutes longer or until heated through.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a large pan, stir until it boils.
Boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 teaspoon soda.
Pour over popped corn.
Bake in two 9 x 13-inch pans for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Wash and break cauliflower and broccoli into small pieces. Add other ingredients.
Pour Italian dressing over mixture.
Toss together.
Let set.
When ready to serve, add fresh tomatoes.

title: grace's fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Line angel food cake pan with waxed paper.
Pour batter into pan. Put 1/2 gallon water in pressure cooker and cook at 12 pounds pressure for 1 1/2 hours. Bake in a 225° oven for 25 minutes.
Store in a cool place for at least 2 weeks.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add all dry ingredients and mix well; then add oil, eggs, vanilla, zucchini and nuts.
Pour into well greased loaf pans. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: marinated 12 chicken boneless breasts
directions: Mix together sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, celery seed, paprika, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken into mixture.
Marinate overnight.

title: perfect sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, oil, sugar and confectioners sugar in large bowl until light.
Add vanilla, baking soda, cream of tartar, eggs and salt.
Mix well.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Chill for 4 hours or longer.
Shape into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Flatten into bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes or until light brown.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: baked beans(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Brown ground meat in olive oil in skillet. Mix all remaining ingredients together and add to browned meat. Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish or bean pot and bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: marilyn's meat dip
directions: Brown and drain ground chuck.
Combine with chili and Velveeta in small casserole dish.
Cover and warm in microwave until cheese is melted.
Stir.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In a large bowl, microwave margarine until melted.
Stir in sugar and vanilla.
Stir in eggs, one at a time.
Add cocoa mix.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until brownies pull away from sides of pan.
Cool completely.
Cut into squares.

title: dieter vegetable soup
directions: Chop all vegetables coarsely.
Add water and bouillon cubes. Bring to a boil, then simmer about 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Contains 145 calories per serving.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter until soft (about 3 minutes). Mix with next 6 ingredients.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Combine potato chips, cheese and almonds; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a crock-pot.
Let bubble on low for 4 to 6 hours.
Serves 4.

title: brine for smoking salmon or trout
directions: Marinate overnight.
Rinse fish thoroughly and let air dry approximately 1 hour.
Smoke 4 to 6 hours depending on size of fish.
Pierce skin before smoking.

title: shrimp fettuccine
directions: Clean and devein shrimp.
Season with salt, pepper and Tony's seasoning.
Set aside.
Start cooking the noodles.
Saute butter with garlic.
Add shrimp and cook until pink.
Add cream and simmer 5 minutes.
Slowly add both cheeses, stirring.
Add noodles and simmer 2 minutes.
Serve with French bread.
(Cooking time, 20 minutes.)

title: ham and potatoes au gratin
directions: Spray a slow cooker with butter flavored cooking spray. Combine ham, potatoes and onion. Sprinkle cheese evenly over top.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: quick and easy broccoli soup
directions: Combine all into a large pot and heat slowly for 1 to 2 hours until thickened.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.
Feeds 8 to 10.
Good served with barbecue sandwiches.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Grease a large baking dish and line bottom with dried beef. Mix sour cream and soup together.
Place chicken on beef and pour mixture over the chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cracker pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except egg whites.
Fold in whites. Pour into a greased 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no bake banana split pie
directions: Mix together and press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Chill for 1 hour.

title: saturday noodle bake
directions: Brown meats in margarine; add onion and cook until tender. Add soup, cream cheese, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings; simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles, drain.
Place noodles in 11 x 7-inch buttered baking dish.
Pour sauce over noodles.
Mix cornflakes with melted butter; sprinkle over top. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: swiss and chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch dish and cover each piece with a slice of cheese.
Mix water and soup; pour over chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle stuffing over soup and drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake 1 hour, uncovered, at 350°.

title: gooie butter cake
directions: Mix cake
mix,	oleo
and
eggs
together.
Put cake batter into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Mix together powdered sugar,
cream
cheese, vanilla and 2 eggs.	Pour over top of cake mixture
and
bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Reserve some of topping and nuts.
Cream together cream cheese, Cool Whip and peanut butter, sugar and vanilla.
Pour in 2 crusts.
Top with Cool Whip.
Put nuts on top; freeze.
Will keep for weeks in freezer.
Thaw in refrigerator for 1 hour before serving.

title: date balls
directions: Cook brown sugar, oleo, white sugar, and dates together for 6 minutes or until dates have mixed well.
Add coconut, nuts, and Rice Krispies.
While warm, form into balls and roll in powdered sugar or coconut.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Cut Milky Way candy bars into small pieces.
Combine candy bar pieces and Eagle Brand in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until smooth; remove from heat, then add chocolate syrup and 1 quart of milk.
Heat until blended.
Pour mixture into 1 gallon freezer can; add milk to fill line.
Freeze in electric or hand freezer.

title: potato delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, melt margarine.
Mix all other ingredients, except 1/2 cup potato chips.
Pour into melted margarine; top with remaining potato chips.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: baptist champagne
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: iced tea
directions: Stove Top:
Bring saucepan of water to boil.
When water is boiling, drop tea bags in and boil for 10 minutes.
Put sugar and lemonade mix in 1 gallon pitcher.
Pour tea in pitcher and fill with cold water; stir.
Chill and serve.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Mix all items together, except cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Place in pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Mix cheese and sauce together and place on top of pie.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: dang good pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set and slightly brown on top.

title: pacific lime mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and add pineapple juice.
Chill until slighlty thickened, then beat until frothy.
Fold in pineapple.
Add cottage cheese, horseradish, whipped cream and nuts.
Chill in mold for at least two hours or overnight.
Unmold onto lettuce bed.
Fill center with pineapple chunks.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix the 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg and 3 teaspoons sugar separately.

title: our best fried rice
directions: In a medium skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Set aside.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons drippings. To drippings in skillet, add green peppers and onion; saute 3 minutes.
Add rice and stir-fry until golden brown about 5 minutes.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, salt, and reserved bacon. Heat until hot.

title: good ole pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco until fluffy, add sugar, then add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Add flavors; add milk and flour alternately beating well.
Bake time:
One hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: german potato salad
directions: Brown bacon and take
out
of pan.
Saute onion in fat. Add flour until bubbly and slowly stirring add water, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add
bacon
and
simmer
a
couple of minutes. Pour over potatoes and eggs.
Serve warm.

title: sausage cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into small (1 to 1 1/2-inch) balls.
